<div id="content_wrapper" class="longformpage">
	<!-- <h2></h2> -->
			<div class="longform post_img fullwidth">
			<img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/bestbookcovers2024-copy.jpg" alt="" class="entry_post"/>
		</div>
				<h1>The 167 Best Book Covers of 2024</h1>
		<h2>According to 54 Book Cover Designers</h2>
    <div class="inner">
		<div class="post_header_wrapper">
    				</div>
				<div class="author_info" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
			<div class="author_name">By&nbsp;<a href="https://lithub.com/author/emily-temple/" itemprop="url"><span itemprop="name">Emily&nbsp;Temple</span></a></div>
			<div class="author_hr"><hr/></div>
			<div class="publish_date">December 24, 2024</div>
		</div>
		<div class="social_links">
						<a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?via=lithub&text=The+167+Best+Book+Covers+of+2024&url=https%3A%2F%2Flithub.com%2Fthe-167-best-book-covers-of-2024%2F"><span class="social_twitter"></span></a>
			<a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flithub.com%2Fthe-167-best-book-covers-of-2024%2F&t=The+167+Best+Book+Covers+of+2024"><span class="social_facebook"></span></a>
					</div>
    <div class="inner">
    	<!-- Begin main content -->
    	<div class="inner_wrapper fullwidth">
    			
										<!-- Begin each blog post -->
						<div class="post_wrapper" style="padding-top:0;">
							<div class="post_inner_wrapper">
						    	<div class="post_wrapper_inner">
										<div class="inner_wrapper fullwidth">
								        
										<p>As is now <a href="https://lithub.com/tag/best-book-covers-of-the-year" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Literary Hub tradition</a>, I am pleased to present the best book covers of the year–as chosen by some of the industry’s best book cover designers.</p><div class="insert-post-ads" style="clear:both;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><span>Article continues after advertisement</span><script id="9b7a21a47fb44523b011db6d4f4cad23">(new Image()).src = 'https://capi.connatix.com/tr/si?token=546998bb-b9c0-4480-8c91-3e307220efff&cid=86b7c382-5e20-4129-84db-dea768f4d688';  cnx.cmd.push(function() {    cnx({      playerId: "546998bb-b9c0-4480-8c91-3e307220efff"    }).render("9b7a21a47fb44523b011db6d4f4cad23");  });</script></div><div class="insert-post-ads remove"><a href="https://lithub.memberful.com/join" target="_new" class="remove-ads external">Remove Ads</a></div>
<p>This year, I asked 54 designers to share their favorite covers of the year, and they came back with a grand total of 167 covers (<em>NB:</em> for the purposes of this list, series concepts will be counted as single covers), representing work by 105 different designers for 83 different imprints at home and abroad. This year, there was somewhat less consensus than usual–the first place citation only got 8 mentions, compared to last year&#8217;s 12, and only 62 covers were selected by more than one designer, leaving over 100 selected by only one–which ultimately just means we have more exciting book covers to look at than ever. All of the designers’ choices, and their comments, are below.</p>
<p>But first . . . the stats.</p>
<h1><strong>The stats:</strong></h1>
<h2><strong>The best of the best book covers:</strong></h2>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>First place (8 mentions):</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Jeff VanderMeer, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250824042" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Southern Reach series</a> (10th Anniversary redesign)<br />
design by <strong>Pablo Delcan</strong> (Picador, July)</p><div class="insert-post-ads" style="clear:both;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><span>Article continues after advertisement</span><div class="htlad-LH_PP_IC"></div></div><div class="insert-post-ads remove"><a href="https://lithub.memberful.com/join" target="_new" class="remove-ads external">Remove Ads</a></div>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Second place (tie–7 mentions each):</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Kaveh Akbar, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593537619" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Martyr!</em></a><br />
design by <strong>Linda Huang</strong> (Knopf, January)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Liz Moore, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593418918" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The God of the Woods</a><br />
</em>design by <strong>Grace Han</strong> (Riverhead, July)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p><div class="insert-post-ads" style="clear:both;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><span>Article continues after advertisement</span><div class="htlad-LH_PP_IC"></div></div><div class="insert-post-ads remove"><a href="https://lithub.memberful.com/join" target="_new" class="remove-ads external">Remove Ads</a></div>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Third place (tie–6 mentions each):</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">Solvej Balle, tr. Barbara J. Haveland, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237253" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>On the Calculation of Volume</em></a> (Books 1 &amp; 2)<br />
design by <strong>Matt Dorfman</strong> (New Directions, November)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8216;Pemi Aguda, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781324065852" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Ghostroots</a><br />
</em>design by <strong>Sarahmay Wilkinson</strong>, art by Day Briere (W.W. Norton, May)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<h2><strong>The presses with the most covers on the list:</strong></h2>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>First place:<br />
</em><strong>New Directions </strong>(14 books)</p><div class="insert-post-ads" style="clear:both;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><span>Article continues after advertisement</span><div class="htlad-LH_PP_IC"></div></div><div class="insert-post-ads remove"><a href="https://lithub.memberful.com/join" target="_new" class="remove-ads external">Remove Ads</a></div>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Second place:<br />
</em><strong>Knopf </strong>(7 books)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Third place (three-way tie):<br />
</em><strong>Riverhead</strong> (6 books)<br />
<strong>Astra House</strong> (6 books)<br />
<strong>FSG</strong> (6 books)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p><div class="insert-post-ads" style="clear:both;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><span>Article continues after advertisement</span><div class="htlad-LH_PP_IC"></div></div><div class="insert-post-ads remove"><a href="https://lithub.memberful.com/join" target="_new" class="remove-ads external">Remove Ads</a></div>
<h2><strong>The designers with the most different covers on the list:</strong></h2>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>First place:<br />
</em><strong>Alex Merto </strong>(6 covers)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Second place (tie):<br />
</em><strong>Luke Bird </strong>(5 covers)<br />
<strong>Janet Hansen </strong>(5 covers)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Third place (tie):<br />
</em><strong>Tyler Comrie </strong>(4 covers)<br />
<strong>Suzanne Dean</strong> (4 covers)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<h2><strong>The best month for book covers:</strong></h2>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>First place:<br />
</em><strong>September</strong> (23 covers)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Second place:<br />
</em><strong>October</strong> (22 covers)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Third place:<br />
</em><strong>July</strong> (20 covers)</p>
<h1>*</h1>
<h1><strong>The full list:</strong></h1>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250824042" class="external" target="_blank"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246486" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/vandermeer-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/vandermeer-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="915,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="vandermeer copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Jeff VanderMeer, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250824042&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Southern Reach series&lt;/a&gt; (10th Anniversary redesign); cover designs by Pablo Delcan (Picador, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/vandermeer-copy-300x148.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/vandermeer-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246486" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/vandermeer-copy.jpg" alt="" width="915" height="450" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/vandermeer-copy.jpg 915w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/vandermeer-copy-300x148.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/vandermeer-copy-768x378.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/vandermeer-copy-60x30.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/vandermeer-copy-50x25.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 915px) 100vw, 915px" /></a> Jeff VanderMeer, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250824042" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Southern Reach series</a> (10th Anniversary redesign); cover designs by Pablo Delcan (Picador, July)</span>
<p>If you hand Pablo Delcan a brief that includes “biological contaminants,” “peculiar creatures,” and a greenlight for holographic foil, he’s going to knock it out of the park. That fact is as immutable as there will be weather tomorrow. These covers are unlike any others I’ve seen and their hideous beauty feels perfectly matched to the writing.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jasonarias.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jason Arias</a></em></p>
<p>This new cover and series redesign fit the books so well&#8230;the holographic foil! The distorted animals! I can’t get over it.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jayanicely.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jaya Nicely</a></em></p>
<p>The whole trilogy is a work of art. This cover is brilliant, beautiful and terrifying.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://annamorrison.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Anna Morrison</a></em></p>
<p>Perfectly weird covers to match its perfectly weird contents. Such a good blend of creepy and beautiful.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://dana-li.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Dana Li</a></em></p>
<p>It is so striking. The use of foil is not redundant but adds to both theme and effect.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jowoho.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joan Wong</a></em></p>
<p>Incredibly weird, which is so right for this series of beautifully and deeply weird, opaque books.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<p>Mesmerizing art ✔️, holographic foil ✔️, sculpt emboss ✔️. This one is for the collectors.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://junepark.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">June Park</a></em></p>
<p>I am very jealous that Pablo got to design this cover. But I am not mad because it&#8217;s so good. But Pablo if you&#8217;re reading this, I am jealous of you.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://erikcarter.net/#/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Erik Carter</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593537619" class="external" target="_blank"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246537" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/710x5-am1-l-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/710X5-Am1-L._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="987,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Kaveh Akbar martyr" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Kaveh Akbar, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593537619&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Martyr!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Linda Huang (Knopf, January)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/710X5-Am1-L._SL1500_-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/710X5-Am1-L._SL1500_-674x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246537" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/710X5-Am1-L._SL1500_-674x1024.jpg" alt="Kaveh Akbar martyr" width="674" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/710X5-Am1-L._SL1500_-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/710X5-Am1-L._SL1500_-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/710X5-Am1-L._SL1500_-768x1167.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/710X5-Am1-L._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/710X5-Am1-L._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/710X5-Am1-L._SL1500_.jpg 987w" sizes="(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px" /></a> Kaveh Akbar, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593537619" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Martyr!</em></a>; cover design by Linda Huang (Knopf, January)</span>
<p>The figure saying “a novel” was perfect, but the addition of “New York Times bestseller” in a speech bubble took this to a whole new level.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.stephenbrayda.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Stephen Brayda</a></em></p>
<p>Great use of negative space. Clever way to add a bestselling line.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jowoho.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joan Wong</a></em></p>
<p>Eye-catching! Minimal! Negative space!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.vivianrowe.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Vivian Lopez Rowe</a></em></p>
<p>Boldness and restraint in equal measure—an instant classic.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.devingrosz.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Devin Grosz</a></em></p>
<p>Iconic.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://arshraziuddin.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Arsh Raziuddin</a></em></p>
<p><em>Martyr!</em> by Kaveh Akbar succeeds in making its 2-color palette feel rich. And like <em>Model Home</em> it feels like a throwback, but refreshed for 2024. The oversized, condensed serifs are as sharp as the cartoon character’s blade ought to be! I love that the publisher embraced the designer’s restraint—leaving all that bare, unexamined space for the main character and reader to explore.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://charlottestrick.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Charlotte Strick</a></em></p>
<p><em>Martyr!</em> was the most memorable cover of the year for me. So fun and perfect in every way.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://junepark.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">June Park</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231490" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/81pnw3ra40l-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81PNW3RA40L._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="994,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Liz Moore, The God of the Woods" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Liz Moore, The God of the Woods; cover design by Grace Han (Riverhead, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81PNW3RA40L._SL1500_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81PNW3RA40L._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231490" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81PNW3RA40L._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg" alt="Liz Moore, The God of the Woods" width="679" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81PNW3RA40L._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg 679w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81PNW3RA40L._SL1500_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81PNW3RA40L._SL1500_-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81PNW3RA40L._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81PNW3RA40L._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81PNW3RA40L._SL1500_.jpg 994w" sizes="(max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px" /> Liz Moore, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593418918" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The God of the Woods</a></em>; cover design by Grace Han (Riverhead, July)</span>
<p>This one has already been comped a million times in our cover meeting, for good reason! I also loved the read and understanding the symbolism of the pink paint drip made me love the cover even more.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.casandragonzales.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Cassie Gonzales Vu</a></em></p>
<p>After reading this book—I love the pink drip for what it represents. So subtle, a little creepy, and just hits the mark.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kelly-winton.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kelly Winton</a></em></p>
<p>I’m sure this will top the lists everywhere. There is something about that bubble gum pink drip on the green painting that no one can stop thinking about. Am I supposed to feel this way?&#8230;I’m not sure of the feeling I’m feeling when I look at that drip.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/robinbillz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Robin Bilardello</a></em></p>
<p>This cover manages to hit so many notes—it’s atmospheric, taut, beautiful, ominous, inviting. An incredible balancing act.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.laurenpc.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lauren Peters-Collaer</a></em></p>
<p>I was instantly inspired to learn more about the book and to see if I could gleen what that perfect clean pink drip represented. I did not figure that out of course <em>but</em> I was brought to the purchase page, which is a win. This design is toggling the thriller and literary fiction crossover genre so well with the wise use of this particular typeface. I also love how the art extended itself well to the publisher&#8217;s marketing materials.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.nicolecaputo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Nicole Caputo</a></em></p>
<p>That pink drip! It&#8217;s perfect.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.emilymahon.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Emily Mahon</a></em></p>
<p>Love the contrast of imagery here, and the use of vertical space. Don&#8217;t think I&#8217;ve seen classical oil painting upcycled like this before, and in such a satisfying, tactile way.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://davidlitmandesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">David Litman</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237253" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246143" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-10-best-book-covers-of-november-4/calculation-of-colume-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/calculation-of-colume-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1265,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="calculation of colume copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Solvej Balle, tr. Barbara J. Haveland, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237253&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;On the Calculation of Volume&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (Books 1 &amp;amp; 2); cover design by Matt Dorfman (New Directions, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/calculation-of-colume-copy-300x237.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/calculation-of-colume-copy-1240x980.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246143" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/calculation-of-colume-copy-1240x980.jpg" alt="" width="1240" height="980" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/calculation-of-colume-copy-1240x980.jpg 1240w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/calculation-of-colume-copy-300x237.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/calculation-of-colume-copy-768x607.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/calculation-of-colume-copy-60x47.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/calculation-of-colume-copy-50x40.jpg 50w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/calculation-of-colume-copy.jpg 1265w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1240px) 100vw, 1240px" /></a> Solvej Balle, tr. Barbara J. Haveland, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237253" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>On the Calculation of Volume</em></a> (Books 1 &amp; 2); cover design by Matt Dorfman (New Directions, November)</span>
<p>If there was such a thing as an anti-2024 book cover, this is it. No large type or remnants of a human element,<br />
yet still so emotional and warm. I’m both in awe and my heart is sinking. Love it, a lot.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.janet-hansen.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Janet Hansen</a></em></p>
<p>A colorful little squiggly thing, circumscribed by a ribbon of type: how else do you calculate volume?</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://chasematt.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Matt Chase</a></em></p>
<p>A really lovely series design, so soft and warm.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://bendenzer.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Ben Denzer</a></em></p>
<p>VERY classy gradients.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jowoho.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joan Wong</a></em></p>
<p>I’m already a sucker for time loops; this dizzily otherworldly constrained/unconstrained aura seals the deal.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<p>Love the mix of organic and geometric forms here. Plus small type working beautifully. The design speaks volumes!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://davidlitmandesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">David Litman</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781324065852" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="245202" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/meet-the-2024-national-book-award-finalists/ghostroots-pemi-aguda/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/ghostroots-pemi-aguda.jpg" data-orig-size="658,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="ghostroots pemi aguda" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;&#8216;Pemi Aguda, &lt;em&gt;Ghostroots&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sarahmay Wilkinson (W.W. Norton, May)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/ghostroots-pemi-aguda-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/ghostroots-pemi-aguda.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-245202" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/ghostroots-pemi-aguda.jpg" alt="" width="658" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/ghostroots-pemi-aguda.jpg 658w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/ghostroots-pemi-aguda-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/ghostroots-pemi-aguda-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/ghostroots-pemi-aguda-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 658px) 100vw, 658px" /></a> &#8216;Pemi Aguda, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781324065852" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Ghostroots</a></em>; cover design by Sarahmay Wilkinson, art by Day Briere (W.W. Norton, May)</span>
<p>On first glance I was convinced this was a Jane’s Addiction album from the 90s. Surprise, it’s not. And after a playlist deep-dive I could not find anything remotely resembling it, but still can’t shake the familiar feeling, which tangentially fits the theme of being haunted by the past. I love the dark fairytale imagery, block print border, and stretched type.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jasonarias.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jason Arias</a></em></p>
<p>In this first year of AI overlord/overload, I feel myself yearning for evidence of the human hand—and this cover delivers. The bold, commanding typography feels refreshingly unconventional, and that pop of red in Day Briere’s art is the perfect finishing touch. My fave cover of the year.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://milanbozic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Milan Božić</a></em></p>
<p>The textures and patterns of the illustration are gorgeous, and the minimal colors are used so well. The type mirrors the energy of the illustration while still letting it shine. It all comes together so beautifully.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://dana-li.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Dana Li</a></em></p>
<p>Really wonderful execution and use of art and ornament. The simple choice of setting “Ghost” in a more condensed face brings this design to life.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="http://www.linda-huang.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Linda Huang</a></em></p>
<p>I love the poster-like effect of this composition. The type treatment beautifully compliments the art without overpowering it.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.alisonforner.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alison Forner</a></em></p>
<p>The cover for &#8216;Pemi Aguda’s story collection <em>Ghostroots</em> took me back to my art school days of hoarding woodblock-printed alphabets and seeking their digital variants with names like Poplar and Oak. I was charmed by the designer’s instinct to combine that chipboard-esthetic with African ornament and full-color illustration. The sweet fawn resting in a bed of Ben-Day dots begged me not to pass it by.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://charlottestrick.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Charlotte Strick</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238472" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246517" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/41qnrgfzpl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/41QNrgfZPL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="640,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="love junkie" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Love Junkie&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/41QNrgfZPL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-192x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/41QNrgfZPL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246517" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/41QNrgfZPL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="love junkie" width="640" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/41QNrgfZPL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 640w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/41QNrgfZPL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-192x300.jpg 192w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/41QNrgfZPL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/41QNrgfZPL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a> Robert Plunket, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238472" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Love Junkie</a></em>; cover design by Oliver Munday (New Directions, May)</span>
<p>Smart! Cheeky!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.janet-hansen.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Janet Hansen</a></em></p>
<p>Butt!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://erikcarter.net/#/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Erik Carter</a></em></p>
<p>Nice bum.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://annamorrison.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Anna Morrison</a></em></p>
<p>Bottoms up.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<p>Just when I thought I didn’t need to see any more pink background covers…perfect!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.mathmonahan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Math Monahan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781638931089" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="237696" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-14-best-book-covers-of-may/91suzy8dsyl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91suZy8DSyL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Holly Wilson, Kittentits; cover design by Eli Mock (Zando/Gillian Flynn Books, May 21)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Holly Wilson, Kittentits; cover design by Eli Mock (Zando/Gillian Flynn Books, May)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91suZy8DSyL._SL1500_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91suZy8DSyL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-237696" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91suZy8DSyL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" alt="Holly Wilson, Kittentits; cover design by Eli Mock (Zando/Gillian Flynn Books, May 21)" width="683" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91suZy8DSyL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91suZy8DSyL._SL1500_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91suZy8DSyL._SL1500_-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91suZy8DSyL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91suZy8DSyL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91suZy8DSyL._SL1500_.jpg 1000w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></a> Holly Wilson, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781638931089" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kittentits</a></em>; cover design by Eli Mock (Zando/Gillian Flynn Books, May)</span>
<p>The photocopied paper effect lends a gritty tone. Fun, irreverent imagery and color palette.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kimberlyglyder.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kimberly Glyder</a></em></p>
<p>So fun, so punk and I love a cat reference :)</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kelly-winton.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kelly Winton</a></em></p>
<p>I love the retro xerox/90s feel here.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.laurenpc.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lauren Peters-Collaer</a></em></p>
<p>Perfectly encapsulates the vibe of a xeroxed, 90s zine.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.bethsteidle.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Beth Steidle</a></em></p>
<p>The gritty xeroxed texture, the cat face with single tear, and the restrained palette is all so good, alongside that amazing title.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.emilymahon.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Emily Mahon</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593190265" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231471" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/91h21wrbzkl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91h21wrbZkL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="992,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Miranda July, All Fours" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Miranda July, All Fours&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91h21wrbZkL._SL1500_-198x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91h21wrbZkL._SL1500_-677x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231471" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91h21wrbZkL._SL1500_-677x1024.jpg" alt="Miranda July, All Fours" width="677" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91h21wrbZkL._SL1500_-677x1024.jpg 677w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91h21wrbZkL._SL1500_-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91h21wrbZkL._SL1500_-768x1161.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91h21wrbZkL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91h21wrbZkL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91h21wrbZkL._SL1500_.jpg 992w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 677px) 100vw, 677px" /></a> Miranda July, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593190265" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">All Fours</a></em>; cover design by Helen Yentus (Riverhead, May)</span>
<p>This cover completely captivated me from the moment I first saw it. I’m confident this will be the crowd favorite. From the inventive hand-made type to the art selection and color palette, everything just works.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://milanbozic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Milan Božić</a></em></p>
<p>The type takes you on a tour around the cover and then becomes a gateway to the painting lying beneath, it&#8217;s perfectly balanced.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jacksmyth.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jack Smyth</a></em></p>
<p>I love how the hand drawn type pushes out to become a frame.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://bendenzer.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Ben Denzer</a></em></p>
<p>I love how considered the lettering is, yet it also feels so loose and spirited. The juxtaposition of painted modern type with the classical painting makes it so eye catching.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.emilymahon.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Emily Mahon</a></em></p>
<p>Sublime.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668045145" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231463" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/the-ministry-of-time-9781668045145_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/the-ministry-of-time-9781668045145_hr.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2113" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Kailane Bradley, The Ministry of Time" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Kaliane Bradley, The Ministry of Time; cover design by Alison Forner, typography by Andrew Footit (Avid Reader Press, May 7)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/the-ministry-of-time-9781668045145_hr-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/the-ministry-of-time-9781668045145_hr-678x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231463" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/the-ministry-of-time-9781668045145_hr-678x1024.jpg" alt="Kailane Bradley, The Ministry of Time" width="678" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/the-ministry-of-time-9781668045145_hr-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/the-ministry-of-time-9781668045145_hr-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/the-ministry-of-time-9781668045145_hr-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/the-ministry-of-time-9781668045145_hr-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/the-ministry-of-time-9781668045145_hr-1018x1536.jpg 1018w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/the-ministry-of-time-9781668045145_hr-1357x2048.jpg 1357w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/the-ministry-of-time-9781668045145_hr-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/the-ministry-of-time-9781668045145_hr.jpg 1400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 678px) 100vw, 678px" /></a> Kaliane Bradley, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668045145" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Ministry of Time</a></em>; cover design by Alison Forner, typography by Andrew Footit (Avid Reader Press, May)</span>
<p>Dynamic, beautiful use of typography to create movement and depth.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kimberlyglyder.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kimberly Glyder</a></em></p>
<p>I love the overall simplicity of this design and the color palette. The subtle mashing of time periods in the different elements is so clever!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://laurenharms.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lauren Harms</a></em></p>
<p>Love this 3-D type treatment floating in space.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jayamiceli.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jaya Miceli</a></em></p>
<p>Favorite cover and favorite type of year!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/jennycarrow_covers/?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jenny Carrow</a></em></p>
<p>I’m always a sucker for 3-D typography. This is my new favorite. Sorry, <em>Breakfast of Champions</em>.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://davidlitmandesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">David Litman</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593537206" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246594" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/36-ways-of-writing-a-vietnamese-poem/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/36-ways-of-writing-a-vietnamese-poem.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="36 ways of writing a vietnamese poem" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Nam Le, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593537206&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;36 Ways of Writing a Vietnamese Poem&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; design by Janet Hansen (Knopf, March)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/36-ways-of-writing-a-vietnamese-poem-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/36-ways-of-writing-a-vietnamese-poem.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246594" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/36-ways-of-writing-a-vietnamese-poem.jpeg" alt="36 ways of writing a vietnamese poem" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/36-ways-of-writing-a-vietnamese-poem.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/36-ways-of-writing-a-vietnamese-poem-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/36-ways-of-writing-a-vietnamese-poem-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/36-ways-of-writing-a-vietnamese-poem-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Nam Le, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593537206" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">36 Ways of Writing a Vietnamese Poem</a></em>; design by Janet Hansen (Knopf, March)</span>
<p>Brave and satisfyingly brilliant.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.lukebird.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Luke Bird</a></em></p>
<p>I said this almost a decade ago, and I’ll say it again: Janet communicates so much with the barest of moves. The oversized letterforms of the author’s name make a powerful statement about identity. I love the way they contrast beautifully with the small, curvy title. Paired together, they are a work of art—a Franz Kline painting.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="http://www.linda-huang.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Linda Huang</a></em></p>
<p>I&#8217;m just a sucker for a well-executed all-type cover.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://aliciatatone.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alicia Tatone</a></em></p>
<p>NAM. VIET NAM. BIG TYPE? GOOD.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://erikcarter.net/#/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Erik Carter</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593316764" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="233673" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-11-best-book-covers-of-february-2/71-v8uxjp6l-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/71-v8UxjP6L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="673,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Scott Guild, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593316764&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Plastic&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design and illustration by Tyler Comrie (Pantheon, February 13)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Scott Guild, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593316764&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Plastic&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design and illustration by Tyler Comrie (Pantheon, February)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/71-v8UxjP6L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-202x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/71-v8UxjP6L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-233673" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/71-v8UxjP6L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="Scott Guild, Plastic; cover design and illustration by Tyler Comrie (Pantheon, February 13)" width="673" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/71-v8UxjP6L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 673w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/71-v8UxjP6L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-202x300.jpg 202w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/71-v8UxjP6L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/71-v8UxjP6L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-34x50.jpg 34w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 673px) 100vw, 673px" /></a> Scott Guild, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593316764" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Plastic</em></a>; cover design and illustration by Tyler Comrie (Pantheon, February)</span>
<p>I love how playful this is, and the way the chunky letterforms dance around the plastic house.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://dana-li.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Dana Li</a></em></p>
<p>An obviously perfect concept executed perfectly. The weirdness of the &#8216;sim&#8217;-like woman sitting at the edge of the bed really gets me.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.katesinclair.space/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kate Sinclair</a></em></p>
<p>Tyler is so versatile. This is very clever and fresh.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jowoho.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joan Wong</a></em></p>
<p>This concept is fun, fresh, and so well executed.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.emilymahon.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Emily Mahon</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593192368" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231387" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/81ojuoy2f1l-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81OJUoY2f1L._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="994,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Helen Oyeyemi, Parasol Against the Axe" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Helen Oyeyemi, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593192368&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Parasol Against the Axe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Grace Han (Riverhead, March 5)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81OJUoY2f1L._SL1500_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81OJUoY2f1L._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231387" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81OJUoY2f1L._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg" alt="Helen Oyeyemi, Parasol Against the Axe" width="679" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81OJUoY2f1L._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg 679w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81OJUoY2f1L._SL1500_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81OJUoY2f1L._SL1500_-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81OJUoY2f1L._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81OJUoY2f1L._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/81OJUoY2f1L._SL1500_.jpg 994w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px" /></a> Helen Oyeyemi, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593192368" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Parasol Against the Axe</a></em>; cover design by Grace Han (Riverhead, March)</span>
<p>I’m drawn to optical art like a bowerbird to blue, so there’s no denying this one for me. Ignore what I said earlier about theater kid energy, this cover is pure sensory overload and I can’t get enough of it. This feels like the perfect analog to the kaleidoscopic premise and how about that color palette?!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jasonarias.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jason Arias</a></em></p>
<p>I stared at this cover for way too long. Such a treat, especially in person.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://epmock.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Eli Mock</a></em></p>
<p>Every time I see this cover it catches my eye. Great use of color.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://sross.tumblr.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Stephanie Ross</a></em></p>
<p>This design is a striking departure from the author&#8217;s other books, and is unlike any other cover I saw this year. The optical illusion, color palette, and stark geometry all merge in a way that is strangely, surprisingly likeable.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.bethsteidle.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Beth Steidle</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811232227" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="235978" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-11-best-book-covers-of-april-2/61h414-pw0l-_sl1200_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/61H414-pw0L._SL1200_.jpg" data-orig-size="776,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="José Donoso, tr. Leonard Mades, Megan McDowell, Hardie St Martin, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811232227&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;The Obscene Bird of Night&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Joan Wong (New Directions, April 23)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;José Donoso, tr. Leonard Mades, Megan McDowell, Hardie St Martin, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811232227&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;The Obscene Bird of Night&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Joan Wong (New Directions, April 23)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/61H414-pw0L._SL1200_-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/61H414-pw0L._SL1200_-662x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-235978" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/61H414-pw0L._SL1200_-662x1024.jpg" alt="José Donoso, tr. Leonard Mades, Megan McDowell, Hardie St Martin, The Obscene Bird of Night; cover design by Joan Wong (New Directions, April 23)" width="662" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/61H414-pw0L._SL1200_-662x1024.jpg 662w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/61H414-pw0L._SL1200_-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/61H414-pw0L._SL1200_-768x1188.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/61H414-pw0L._SL1200_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/61H414-pw0L._SL1200_-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/61H414-pw0L._SL1200_.jpg 776w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px" /></a> José Donoso, tr. Leonard Mades, Megan McDowell, Hardie St Martin, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811232227" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Obscene Bird of Night</a></em>; cover design by Joan Wong (New Directions, April 23)</span>
<p>Whimsical, wavy, and wonderful.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://sarahschulte.studio/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sarah Schulte</a></em></p>
<p>I love a brown cover, this reminds me of a dream.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://annamorrison.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Anna Morrison</a></em></p>
<p>Is this what happens when you overdose on the absinthe with the convent at the afters?</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://erikcarter.net/#/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Erik Carter</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246588" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/1717596302-900/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1717596302-900.jpg" data-orig-size="900,1440" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="mother naked" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Glen James Brown, &lt;em&gt;Mother Naked&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jon Gray (Peninsula Press, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1717596302-900-188x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1717596302-900-640x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246588" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1717596302-900-640x1024.jpg" alt="mother naked" width="640" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1717596302-900-640x1024.jpg 640w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1717596302-900-188x300.jpg 188w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1717596302-900-768x1229.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1717596302-900-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1717596302-900-31x50.jpg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1717596302-900.jpg 900w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /> Glen James Brown, <em>Mother Naked</em>; cover design by Jon Gray (Peninsula Press, June)</span>
<p>Besides being a huge fan of medieval drawings, I love the playfulness of the interaction between type and figure here, and the unexpected bright green of the background.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.nataliaolbinski.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Natalia Olbinski</a></em></p>
<p>The perfect pairing of old and new; seamless integration of type and image. Jon manages to translate medieval type and imagery into contemporary art.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.alisonforner.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alison Forner</a></em></p>
<p>I have no idea what this book is about, but I wanna read it because the cover looks so damn fun! That sausage pink + acidic green combo makes it even more intriguing.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://junepark.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">June Park</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="234921" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-22-best-book-covers-of-march/a1yqlvpqesl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A1yqlVPqesL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="993,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Cameron Russell, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593595480&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;How to Make Herself Agreeable to Everyone: A Memoir&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Arsh Raziuddin, art direction by Rachel Ake (Random House, March 19)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Cameron Russell, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593595480&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;How to Make Herself Agreeable to Everyone: A Memoir&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Arsh Raziuddin, art direction by Rachel Ake (Random House, March 19)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A1yqlVPqesL._SL1500_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A1yqlVPqesL._SL1500_-678x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-234921" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A1yqlVPqesL._SL1500_-678x1024.jpg" alt="Cameron Russell, How to Make Herself Agreeable to Everyone: A Memoir; cover design by Arsh Raziuddin, art direction by Rachel Ake (Random House, March 19)" width="678" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A1yqlVPqesL._SL1500_-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A1yqlVPqesL._SL1500_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A1yqlVPqesL._SL1500_-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A1yqlVPqesL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A1yqlVPqesL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/A1yqlVPqesL._SL1500_.jpg 993w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 678px) 100vw, 678px" /> Cameron Russell, <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593595480" target="_blank" rel="noopener">How to Make Herself Agreeable to Everyone: A Memoir</a></em>; cover design by Arsh Raziuddin, art direction by Rachel Ake (Random House, March)</span>
<p>Great design and great use of collage. This cover has an intimacy to it that feels fierce and vulnerable.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kelly-winton.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kelly Winton</a></em></p>
<p>Great elements all around. I especially love how the title rephrases depending on how it’s broken.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://laurenharms.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lauren Harms</a></em></p>
<p>Collage has always presented an unfamiliar organic-ness to me. The combination of organic and order is great.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.mathmonahan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Math Monahan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780385550147" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246518" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/81etwkvqql-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81eTwkvQqL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="937,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="zach williams beautiful days uk" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Zach Williams, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780385550147&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Beautiful Days&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Chris Bentham (Hamish Hamilton, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81eTwkvQqL._SL1500_-187x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81eTwkvQqL._SL1500_-640x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246518" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81eTwkvQqL._SL1500_-640x1024.jpg" alt="zach williams beautiful days uk" width="640" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81eTwkvQqL._SL1500_-640x1024.jpg 640w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81eTwkvQqL._SL1500_-187x300.jpg 187w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81eTwkvQqL._SL1500_-768x1229.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81eTwkvQqL._SL1500_-37x60.jpg 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81eTwkvQqL._SL1500_-31x50.jpg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81eTwkvQqL._SL1500_.jpg 937w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a> Zach Williams, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780385550147" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Beautiful Days</a></em>; cover design by Chris Bentham (Hamish Hamilton, July)</span>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="http://www.ZoeNorvell.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Zoe Norvell</a></em></p>
<p>Left no crumbs! Every inch thoughtfully designed, fun, action packed, yet still so clean and balanced.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.janet-hansen.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Janet Hansen</a></em></p>
<p>The movement of the type alongside the collage is excellent.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://aliciatatone.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alicia Tatone</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593241257" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231515" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/91fow5xeeel-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91FoW5XEeeL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Sarah Manguso, Liars" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Sarah Manguso, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593241257&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Liars&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Cassie Gonzales Vu (Hogarth Press, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91FoW5XEeeL._SL1500_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91FoW5XEeeL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231515" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91FoW5XEeeL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" alt="Sarah Manguso, Liars" width="683" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91FoW5XEeeL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91FoW5XEeeL._SL1500_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91FoW5XEeeL._SL1500_-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91FoW5XEeeL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91FoW5XEeeL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91FoW5XEeeL._SL1500_.jpg 1000w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></a> Sarah Manguso, <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593241257" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Liars</a></em>; cover design by Cassie Gonzales Vu (Hogarth Press, July)</span>
<p>Quiet and at the same time audibly hissing with barely contained rage.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://chasematt.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Matt Chase</a></em></p>
<p>I bought this book based on the title and my expertise and experience with the book’s subject, but after I had the book in my hands, my feelings changed. The cover is formidable, but also the fade is everything. It could be the exhaustion of it all, or just the way liars disappear in plain sight, or how we just let them fade away so we can live. I now keep the book face out on the self in my home because the cover.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/robinbillz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Robin Bilardello</a></em></p>
<p>Spot-on type design for Unreliable Narrator / Nature of Stories Itself.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374109288" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231329" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/71aezkcfjvl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71AEZKcFJVL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="978,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Marie-Helene Bertino, Beautyland" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71AEZKcFJVL._SL1500_-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71AEZKcFJVL._SL1500_-668x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231329" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71AEZKcFJVL._SL1500_-668x1024.jpg" alt="Marie-Helene Bertino, Beautyland" width="668" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71AEZKcFJVL._SL1500_-668x1024.jpg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71AEZKcFJVL._SL1500_-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71AEZKcFJVL._SL1500_-768x1178.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71AEZKcFJVL._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71AEZKcFJVL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71AEZKcFJVL._SL1500_.jpg 978w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 668px) 100vw, 668px" /></a> Marie-Helene Bertino, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374109288" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Beautyland</em></a>; cover design by Thomas Colligan (FSG, January)</span>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.heaeunhan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Grace Han</a></em></p>
<p>What a singular thing of beauty. I can’t remember the last time something so graphic felt so astonishing. The playfulness of the script—chef’s kiss!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="http://www.linda-huang.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Linda Huang</a></em></p>
<p>I’m currently reading <em>Beautyland</em>, and I keep flipping back to the cover to look at the title beaming outwards from that tiny point of light in the void—it deepens in meaning with each turn of the page.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.devingrosz.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Devin Grosz</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063355064" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246650" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/sister-snake-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sister-snake-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="sister snake copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Amanda Lee Koe, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063355064&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Sister Snake&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Vivian Lopez Rowe (Ecco, December)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sister-snake-copy-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sister-snake-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246650" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sister-snake-copy.jpg" alt="sister snake copy" width="662" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sister-snake-copy.jpg 662w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sister-snake-copy-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sister-snake-copy-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sister-snake-copy-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px" /></a> Amanda Lee Koe, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063355064" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sister Snake</a></em>; cover design by Vivian Lopez Rowe (Ecco, December)</span>
<p>A design that manages to reference the title in the most unexpected way possible. Also the green background and red nails—electric!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.alisonforner.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alison Forner</a></em></p>
<p>So glad I looked at this week’s releases to spot this one to include! So effective and done confidently. The pared back simplicity works excellently at the blessed thumbnail. And then up close, I’m further intrigued—is it a mannequin? Must read more!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.rachelakedesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Rachel Ake</a></em></p>
<p>Incredibly smart and clever. Love everything about this.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jamesiacobelli.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">James Iacobelli</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593472064" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="234904" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-22-best-book-covers-of-march/71brizoo9pl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/71bRizOO9PL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="993,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="71bRizOO9PL._SL1500_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Marina Yuszczuk, tr. Heather Cleary, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593472064&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Thirst&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Kaitlin Kall (Dutton, March 5)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/71bRizOO9PL._SL1500_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/71bRizOO9PL._SL1500_-678x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-234904" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/71bRizOO9PL._SL1500_-678x1024.jpg" alt="Marina Yuszczuk, tr. Heather Cleary, Thirst (Dutton, March 5)" width="678" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/71bRizOO9PL._SL1500_-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/71bRizOO9PL._SL1500_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/71bRizOO9PL._SL1500_-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/71bRizOO9PL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/71bRizOO9PL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/71bRizOO9PL._SL1500_.jpg 993w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 678px) 100vw, 678px" /></a> Marina Yuszczuk, tr. Heather Cleary, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593472064" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Thirst</a></em>; cover design by Kaitlin Kall (Dutton, March 5)</span>
<p>I love the composition here. The combination of the marble statue against the bright red and pink. The cheeky bite mark. A little scary, a little sexy. So much fun.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://joannemoneill.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joanne O&#8217;Neill</a></em></p>
<p>The contrast of textures: marble statue and punctured paper makes my brain happy. Modernity from history. This cover stuck in my mind all year!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.rachelakedesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Rachel Ake</a></em></p>
<p>I’m a sucker for this color palette. Fun, and makes me want to know more. I want all vampire novels to look like this!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://sross.tumblr.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Stephanie Ross</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238519" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246538" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/258a32e68054467262cc1cbdb9400acb29c1a4b9-6150x9600/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/258a32e68054467262cc1cbdb9400acb29c1a4b9-6150x9600-1.avif" data-orig-size="1000,1561" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="the abyss-6150&#215;9600" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Fernando Vallejo, tr. Yvette Siegert, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238519&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Abyss&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Janet Hansen (New Directions, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/258a32e68054467262cc1cbdb9400acb29c1a4b9-6150x9600-1-192x300.avif" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/258a32e68054467262cc1cbdb9400acb29c1a4b9-6150x9600-1-656x1024.avif" class="size-full wp-image-246538" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/258a32e68054467262cc1cbdb9400acb29c1a4b9-6150x9600-1.avif" alt="the abyss" width="1000" height="1561" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/258a32e68054467262cc1cbdb9400acb29c1a4b9-6150x9600-1.avif 1000w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/258a32e68054467262cc1cbdb9400acb29c1a4b9-6150x9600-1-192x300.avif 192w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/258a32e68054467262cc1cbdb9400acb29c1a4b9-6150x9600-1-656x1024.avif 656w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/258a32e68054467262cc1cbdb9400acb29c1a4b9-6150x9600-1-768x1199.avif 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/258a32e68054467262cc1cbdb9400acb29c1a4b9-6150x9600-1-38x60.avif 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/258a32e68054467262cc1cbdb9400acb29c1a4b9-6150x9600-1-984x1536.avif 984w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/258a32e68054467262cc1cbdb9400acb29c1a4b9-6150x9600-1-32x50.avif 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></a> Fernando Vallejo, tr. Yvette Siegert, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238519" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Abyss</a></em>; cover design by Janet Hansen (New Directions, June)</span>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.heaeunhan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Grace Han</a></em></p>
<p>Everything here clicks for me (and love the split translation copy).</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.stephenbrayda.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Stephen Brayda</a></em></p>
<p>Feels like a haunting question. So beautifully and simply done.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.katesinclair.space/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kate Sinclair</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646222100" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231506" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/6120i5cbzl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/6120I5cBzL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="992,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Yasmin Zaher, The Coin" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Yasmin Zaher, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646222100&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Coin&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Jaya Miceli (Catapult, July 9)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/6120I5cBzL._SL1500_-198x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/6120I5cBzL._SL1500_-677x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231506" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/6120I5cBzL._SL1500_-677x1024.jpg" alt="Yasmin Zaher, The Coin" width="677" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/6120I5cBzL._SL1500_-677x1024.jpg 677w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/6120I5cBzL._SL1500_-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/6120I5cBzL._SL1500_-768x1161.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/6120I5cBzL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/6120I5cBzL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/6120I5cBzL._SL1500_.jpg 992w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 677px) 100vw, 677px" /></a> Yasmin Zaher, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646222100" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Coin</em></a>; cover design by Jaya Miceli (Catapult, July 9)</span>
<p>Every time I see it, I’m mesmerized by the figure (from a photo by Isabelle Wenzel). Weird, beautiful, and set against the most perfect background color.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://joannemoneill.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joanne O&#8217;Neill</a></em></p>
<p>Jaya knows how to put emotion into a book cover one million ways. Iconic photograph + great color.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.janet-hansen.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Janet Hansen</a></em></p>
<p>Such a striking image—I love this bizarre posture.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.laurenpc.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lauren Peters-Collaer</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781644452035" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246522" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/tometherington2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/TomEtherington2.jpg" data-orig-size="977,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="bojan louis sinking bell uk" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Bojan Louis, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781644452035&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Sinking Bell&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Tom Etherington (Dead Ink, February)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/TomEtherington2-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/TomEtherington2-667x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246522" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/TomEtherington2-667x1024.jpg" alt="bojan louis sinking bell uk" width="667" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/TomEtherington2-667x1024.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/TomEtherington2-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/TomEtherington2-768x1179.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/TomEtherington2-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/TomEtherington2-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/TomEtherington2.jpg 977w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Bojan Louis, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781644452035" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sinking Bell</a></em>; cover design by Tom Etherington (Dead Ink, February)</span>
<p>You could spend hours investigating this cover, it reveals so much each time I see it. The imperfections are perfect and I love the frames that aren&#8217;t framing anything.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jacksmyth.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jack Smyth</a></em></p>
<p>It takes a true expert in color to incorporate so many hues at once while still maintaining readable typography</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="http://www.ZoeNorvell.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Zoe Norvell</a></em></p>
<p>Beautifully-executed, vibrant collage. I just love looking at it.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.lukebird.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Luke Bird</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="245698" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/on-the-roof-design-louis-gabaldoni/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/on-the-roof-design-louis-gabaldoni.jpg" data-orig-size="1592,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="on the roof" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Tom Allan, &lt;em&gt;On the Roof&lt;/em&gt;; design by Louis Gabaldoni (Profile Books, August 29)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/on-the-roof-design-louis-gabaldoni-187x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/on-the-roof-design-louis-gabaldoni-637x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-245698 size-large" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/on-the-roof-design-louis-gabaldoni-637x1024.jpg" alt="on the roof" width="637" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/on-the-roof-design-louis-gabaldoni-637x1024.jpg 637w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/on-the-roof-design-louis-gabaldoni-187x300.jpg 187w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/on-the-roof-design-louis-gabaldoni-768x1235.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/on-the-roof-design-louis-gabaldoni-37x60.jpg 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/on-the-roof-design-louis-gabaldoni-955x1536.jpg 955w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/on-the-roof-design-louis-gabaldoni-1274x2048.jpg 1274w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/on-the-roof-design-louis-gabaldoni-31x50.jpg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/on-the-roof-design-louis-gabaldoni.jpg 1592w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 637px) 100vw, 637px" /> Tom Allan, <em>On the Roof</em>; design by Louis Gabaldoni (Profile Books, August)</span>
<p>This made me smile when I saw it, so clever!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.hollyovenden.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Holly Ovenden</a></em></p>
<p>What is more delightful than a book inspiring its own playful objectification <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/C-NFWL2sd7K/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">in this way</a>?</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jasonarias.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jason Arias</a></em></p>
<p>I love the elegance and simplicity of this approach. The cover works on its own terms, but also becomes a house when you start reading it. Brilliant!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.katesinclair.space/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kate Sinclair</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374280567" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="242188" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/suffering-grace-and-redemption-how-the-bronx-came-to-be/paradise-bronx/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/paradise-bronx-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1707,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="paradise bronx" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Ian Frazier, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374280567&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Paradise Bronx&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by TK TK (FSG, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/paradise-bronx-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/paradise-bronx-683x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-242188" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/paradise-bronx-683x1024.jpg" alt="paradise bronx" width="683" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/paradise-bronx-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/paradise-bronx-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/paradise-bronx-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/paradise-bronx-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/paradise-bronx-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/paradise-bronx-1366x2048.jpg 1366w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/paradise-bronx-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/paradise-bronx-scaled.jpg 1707w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></a> Ian Frazier, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374280567" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Paradise Bronx</a></em>; cover design by Thomas Colligan (FSG, August)</span>
<p>Love the tactility and personality of this cover. It almost feels like a real piece of graffiti you&#8217;d see on a random block as you&#8217;re heading towards the subway.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://aliciatatone.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alicia Tatone</a></em></p>
<p>Thomas has such a special talent for making nonfiction covers just as exciting as fiction covers, if not more. I love this maximalist NY moment jam-packed with character.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://junepark.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">June Park</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646222551" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239090" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/ella-baxter-woo-woo/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ella-Baxter-Woo-Woo-.jpeg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Ella Baxter, Woo Woo" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Ella Baxter, Woo Woo; cover design by Nicole Caputo (Catapult, December)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ella-Baxter-Woo-Woo--199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ella-Baxter-Woo-Woo-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239090" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ella-Baxter-Woo-Woo-.jpeg" alt="Ella Baxter, Woo Woo" width="662" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ella-Baxter-Woo-Woo-.jpeg 662w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ella-Baxter-Woo-Woo--199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ella-Baxter-Woo-Woo--40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Ella-Baxter-Woo-Woo--33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px" /></a> Ella Baxter, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646222551" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Woo Woo</a></em>; cover design by Nicole Caputo (Catapult, December)</span>
<p>Stunning typography. It&#8217;s brilliant.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jamesiacobelli.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">James Iacobelli</a></em></p>
<p>I love those jarring green eyes paired with the smart and sexy font and color choices. Startling in the best way &amp; I can&#8217;t look away&#8230;!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://junepark.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">June Park</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780571377671" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246419" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/neu-klang-by-christoph-dallach-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Neu-Klang-by-Christoph-Dallach-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="650,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Neu Klang by Christoph Dallach copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Christoph Dallach, tr. Katy Derbyshire Derbyshire, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780571377671&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Neu Klang&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jack Smyth (Faber &#038; Faber, August 13)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Neu-Klang-by-Christoph-Dallach-copy-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Neu-Klang-by-Christoph-Dallach-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246419" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Neu-Klang-by-Christoph-Dallach-copy.jpg" alt="Neu Klang by Christoph Dallach copy" width="650" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Neu-Klang-by-Christoph-Dallach-copy.jpg 650w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Neu-Klang-by-Christoph-Dallach-copy-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Neu-Klang-by-Christoph-Dallach-copy-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Neu-Klang-by-Christoph-Dallach-copy-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /></a> Christoph Dallach, tr. Katy Derbyshire Derbyshire, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780571377671" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Neu Klang</a></em>; cover design by Jack Smyth (Faber &amp; Faber, August 13)</span>
<p>This one leaves me speechless.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://joannemoneill.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joanne O&#8217;Neill</a></em></p>
<p>Embodies experimental German psychedelic rock beautifully.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://davidlitmandesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">David Litman</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250321701" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246597" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/wolfcovers-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/wolfcovers-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="900,910" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="wolfcovers copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Tom Wolfe paperback reissue series; design by Alex Merto, illustrations by Seymour Chwast (Picador, August &#038; November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/wolfcovers-copy-297x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/wolfcovers-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246597" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/wolfcovers-copy.jpg" alt="" width="900" height="910" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/wolfcovers-copy.jpg 900w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/wolfcovers-copy-297x300.jpg 297w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/wolfcovers-copy-768x777.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/wolfcovers-copy-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/wolfcovers-copy-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/wolfcovers-copy-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/wolfcovers-copy-50x50.jpg 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></a> Tom Wolfe paperback reissue series; design by Alex Merto, illustrations by Seymour Chwast (Picador, August &amp; November)</span>
<p>Of course the legendary Seymour Chwast was the perfect illustrator for these reissues, but I’d like to also call attention to Alex’s design system–from the wry typeface to the clean, horizontal rules. They feel fresh and frame the illustrations into collectable classics.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="http://www.linda-huang.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Linda Huang</a></em></p>
<p>When a redesigned backlist makes you want to buy them all, the design is definitely working.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/jennycarrow_covers/?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jenny Carrow</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246417" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/812wuoukl9l-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/812WuOUkL9L._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="955,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="not waving but drowning" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Stevie Smith, &lt;em&gt;Not Waving but Drowning&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Pete Adlington (Faber &#038; Faber, October 10)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/812WuOUkL9L._SL1500_-191x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/812WuOUkL9L._SL1500_-652x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246417" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/812WuOUkL9L._SL1500_-652x1024.jpg" alt="not waving but drowning" width="652" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/812WuOUkL9L._SL1500_-652x1024.jpg 652w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/812WuOUkL9L._SL1500_-191x300.jpg 191w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/812WuOUkL9L._SL1500_-768x1206.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/812WuOUkL9L._SL1500_-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/812WuOUkL9L._SL1500_-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/812WuOUkL9L._SL1500_.jpg 955w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px" /> Stevie Smith, <em>Not Waving but Drowning</em>; cover design by Pete Adlington (Faber &amp; Faber, October)</span>
<p>So cute, so simple, so pure. I’m immediately drawn in and must know every emotion this little frog is feeling.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.mathmonahan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Math Monahan</a></em></p>
<p>So sweet, so sad. Darkly funny, much like Stevie’s poetry.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://joannemoneill.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joanne O&#8217;Neill</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593712948" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239021" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/olga-tokarczuk-the-empusium/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Olga-Tokarczuk-The-Empusium.jpeg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Olga Tokarczuk, The Empusium" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Olga Tokarczuk, tr. Antonia Lloyd-Jones, The Empusium: A Health Resort Horror Story; cover design by Lauren Peters-Collaer (Riverhead, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Olga-Tokarczuk-The-Empusium-199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Olga-Tokarczuk-The-Empusium.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239021" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Olga-Tokarczuk-The-Empusium.jpeg" alt="Olga Tokarczuk, tr. Antonia Lloyd-Jones, The Empusium: A Health Resort Horror Story" width="662" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Olga-Tokarczuk-The-Empusium.jpeg 662w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Olga-Tokarczuk-The-Empusium-199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Olga-Tokarczuk-The-Empusium-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Olga-Tokarczuk-The-Empusium-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px" /></a> Olga Tokarczuk, tr. Antonia Lloyd-Jones, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593712948" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Empusium</a></em>; cover design by Lauren Peters-Collaer (Riverhead, September)</span>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.bethsteidle.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Beth Steidle</a></em></p>
<p>Mesmerizing, but also, how did you get this approved? Asking for a friend.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.mathmonahan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Math Monahan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246734" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/bolano-3/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/bolano.jpg" data-orig-size="900,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="bolano reissues" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Bolaño reissues (&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250321749&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;By Night in Chile&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;/&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250898166&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Antwerp&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;/&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250898180&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Return&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;); cover design by Michael Schmelliym, illustrations by Mike Adams (Picador, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/bolano-300x150.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/bolano.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246734" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/bolano.jpg" alt="bolano reissues" width="900" height="450" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/bolano.jpg 900w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/bolano-300x150.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/bolano-768x384.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/bolano-60x30.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/bolano-50x25.jpg 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /> Bolaño reissues (<em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250321749" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">By Night in Chile</a></em>/<em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250898166" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Antwerp</a></em>/<em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250898180" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Return</a></em>); cover design by Michael Schmelling, illustrations by Mike Adams (Picador, September)</span>
<p>Imagine a grubby corner bookshop with a rack for local zines—these would fit in fairly well, I wish to acquire them all.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<p>Perfect oddballs! I love them!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://aliciatatone.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alicia Tatone</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237956" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="243289" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/footnotes-all-the-way-down-how-russian-poetry-mines-the-past-to-reveal-the-present/gander-mojave-ghost-rgb/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Gander-MOJAVE-GHOST-rgb.jpg" data-orig-size="1500,2400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Gander MOJAVE GHOST rgb" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Forrest Gander, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237956&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Mojave Ghost&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Rodrigo Corral (New Directions, October 1)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Gander-MOJAVE-GHOST-rgb-188x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Gander-MOJAVE-GHOST-rgb-640x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-243289" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Gander-MOJAVE-GHOST-rgb-640x1024.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Gander-MOJAVE-GHOST-rgb-640x1024.jpg 640w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Gander-MOJAVE-GHOST-rgb-188x300.jpg 188w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Gander-MOJAVE-GHOST-rgb-768x1229.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Gander-MOJAVE-GHOST-rgb-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Gander-MOJAVE-GHOST-rgb-960x1536.jpg 960w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Gander-MOJAVE-GHOST-rgb-1280x2048.jpg 1280w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Gander-MOJAVE-GHOST-rgb-31x50.jpg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Gander-MOJAVE-GHOST-rgb.jpg 1500w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /></a> Forrest Gander, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237956" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Mojave Ghost</em></a>; cover design by Rodrigo Corral (New Directions, October 1)</span>
<p>I love how the pulp board background transforms into sand and the shadow suddenly comes to life.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.keenandesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jamie Keenan</a></em></p>
<p>So much can be said with so little when the idea is smart. Thank you to the designer for the beauty and simplicity of <em>Mojave Ghost</em> by Forrest Gander. The quiet wit of this cover sings to me.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://charlottestrick.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Charlotte Strick</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374607135" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239042" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/rivers-solomon-model-home/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Rivers-Solomon-Model-Home-.jpeg" data-orig-size="657,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Rivers Solomon, Model Home" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;(MCD, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Rivers-Solomon-Model-Home--197x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Rivers-Solomon-Model-Home-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239042" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Rivers-Solomon-Model-Home-.jpeg" alt="Rivers Solomon, Model Home" width="657" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Rivers-Solomon-Model-Home-.jpeg 657w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Rivers-Solomon-Model-Home--197x300.jpeg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Rivers-Solomon-Model-Home--39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Rivers-Solomon-Model-Home--33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 657px) 100vw, 657px" /></a> Rivers Solomon, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374607135" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Model Home</a></em>; cover design by Alex Merto (MCD, October)</span>
<p>Uncanny and disturbing in the very best way.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.devingrosz.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Devin Grosz</a></em></p>
<p>The cover for <em>Model Home</em> by Rivers Solomon froze me in my airport-bookstore-browsing tracks. Was it the flood of toxic swamp-green overprinted with black? Was it the eerie Alice in Wonderland-sized eye passively peering through the second story window? Or simply the font choice: a 1980s dark alley mashup of medieval Uncial x Victorian Copperplate . . . those truncated capital “S”s slithering up through the suburban lawn? In a word, YES!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://charlottestrick.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Charlotte Strick</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602474" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239146" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-15-best-book-covers-of-june/puloma-ghosh-mouth/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/puloma-ghosh-mouth.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="puloma ghosh mouth" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Puloma Ghosh, &lt;em&gt;Mouth&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Adriana Tonello (Astra House, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/puloma-ghosh-mouth-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/puloma-ghosh-mouth.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239146" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/puloma-ghosh-mouth.jpeg" alt="" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/puloma-ghosh-mouth.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/puloma-ghosh-mouth-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/puloma-ghosh-mouth-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/puloma-ghosh-mouth-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Puloma Ghosh, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602474" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mouth</a></em>; cover design by Adriana Tonello (Astra House, June)</span>
<p>These images are great together and the reduced palette really helps relate them to one another. So minimal and yet so suggestive.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.vivianrowe.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Vivian Lopez Rowe</a></em></p>
<p>This cover makes me squirm, in the best possible way.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237994" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246145" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-10-best-book-covers-of-november-4/attachment/9780811237994/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9780811237994.jpg" data-orig-size="648,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Elias Canetti, &lt;em&gt;The Book Against Death&lt;/em&gt;" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Elias Canetti, tr. Peter Filkins, &lt;em&gt;The Book Against Death&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jamie Keenan (New Directions, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9780811237994-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9780811237994.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246145" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9780811237994.jpg" alt="Elias Canetti, The Book Against Death" width="648" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9780811237994.jpg 648w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9780811237994-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9780811237994-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9780811237994-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 648px) 100vw, 648px" /></a> Elias Canetti, tr. Peter Filkins, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237994" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Book Against Death</a></em>; cover design by Jamie Keenan (New Directions, November)</span>
<p>This cover makes me feel a beloved nostalgia for quieter, more classic designs. In the sea of similarities in cover design we see today, this classic yet modern, smart and intriguing portal is a breath of fresh air. It is bold in its quietness and suits the subject perfectly.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.nicolecaputo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Nicole Caputo</a></em></p>
<p>This brings to mind the haunting ending of the movie <em>The Vanishing</em> (the original one, from 1988, please) but in a much, much more cheerful, <em>Pushing Daisies</em> way. Love.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780385549820" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="235981" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-11-best-book-covers-of-april-2/81ozotawdwl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/81OzoTawDwL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1022,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Anoushka Warden, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780385549820&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;I&#8217;m F*cking Amazing&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover art by Nancy McKie, lettering by Lynn Buckley, art direction by Emily Mahon (Doubleday, April 30)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Anoushka Warden, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780385549820&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;I&#8217;m F*cking Amazing&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover art by Nancy McKie, lettering by Lynn Buckley, art direction by Emily Mahon (Doubleday, April)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/81OzoTawDwL._SL1500_-204x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/81OzoTawDwL._SL1500_-698x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-235981" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/81OzoTawDwL._SL1500_-698x1024.jpg" alt="Anoushka Warden, I'm F*cking Amazing; cover art by Nancy McKie, lettering by Lynn Buckley, art direction by Emily Mahon (Doubleday, April 30)" width="698" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/81OzoTawDwL._SL1500_-698x1024.jpg 698w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/81OzoTawDwL._SL1500_-204x300.jpg 204w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/81OzoTawDwL._SL1500_-768x1127.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/81OzoTawDwL._SL1500_-41x60.jpg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/81OzoTawDwL._SL1500_-34x50.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/81OzoTawDwL._SL1500_.jpg 1022w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 698px) 100vw, 698px" /></a> Anoushka Warden, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780385549820" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>I&#8217;m F*cking Amazing</em></a>; cover art by Nancy McKie, lettering by Lynn Buckley, art direction by Emily Mahon (Doubleday, April)</span>
<p>An amazing combination of just the right imperfectly perfect illustration and hand lettering.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.stephenbrayda.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Stephen Brayda</a></em></p>
<p>A pitch-perfect encapsulation of the title, in all its deadpan hilarity.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.devingrosz.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Devin Grosz</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374168155" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239081" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/richard-price-lazarus-man/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Richard-Price-Lazarus-Man-.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Richard Price, Lazarus Man" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Richard Price, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374168155&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Lazarus Man&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by June Park (FSG, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Richard-Price-Lazarus-Man--200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Richard-Price-Lazarus-Man-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239081" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Richard-Price-Lazarus-Man-.jpeg" alt="Richard Price, Lazarus Man" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Richard-Price-Lazarus-Man-.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Richard-Price-Lazarus-Man--200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Richard-Price-Lazarus-Man--40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Richard-Price-Lazarus-Man--33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Richard Price, <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374168155" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lazarus Man</a></em>; cover design by June Park (FSG, November)</span>
<p>That plume of orange brings this cover to life.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://epmock.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Eli Mock</a></em></p>
<p>Painterly. Classic.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.emilymahon.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Emily Mahon</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593230442" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240892" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-17-best-book-covers-of-july-2/olivia-gatwood-whoever-you-are-honey/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/olivia-gatwood-whoever-you-are-honey.jpg" data-orig-size="993,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="olivia gatwood whoever you are honey" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Olivia Gatwood, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593230442&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Whoever You Are, Honey&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Jaya Miceli, art by Steven Wilson (Dial Press, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/olivia-gatwood-whoever-you-are-honey-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/olivia-gatwood-whoever-you-are-honey-678x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-240892" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/olivia-gatwood-whoever-you-are-honey-678x1024.jpg" alt="" width="678" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/olivia-gatwood-whoever-you-are-honey-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/olivia-gatwood-whoever-you-are-honey-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/olivia-gatwood-whoever-you-are-honey-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/olivia-gatwood-whoever-you-are-honey-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/olivia-gatwood-whoever-you-are-honey-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/olivia-gatwood-whoever-you-are-honey.jpg 993w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 678px) 100vw, 678px" /></a> Olivia Gatwood, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593230442" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Whoever You Are, Honey</em></a>; cover design by Jaya Miceli, art by Steven Wilson (Dial Press, July)</span>
<p>There is an edginess to the melting art as it guides your eye down the cover.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kimberlyglyder.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kimberly Glyder</a></em></p>
<p>This falls squarely into &#8220;covers I experience viscerally&#8221; territory. It&#8217;s almost as if the artwork is melting over the type in real time.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.alisonforner.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alison Forner</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250893697" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="234500" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/but-the-ancient-greeks-didnt-sound-irish-on-capturing-voice-in-historical-fiction/glorious-exploits/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/glorious-exploits.jpeg" data-orig-size="900,1359" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="glorious exploits" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Ferdia Lennon, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250893697&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Glorious Exploits&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Gregg Kulick (Henry Holt, March)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/glorious-exploits-199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/glorious-exploits-678x1024.jpeg" class="size-large wp-image-234500" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/glorious-exploits-678x1024.jpeg" alt="" width="678" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/glorious-exploits-678x1024.jpeg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/glorious-exploits-199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/glorious-exploits-768x1160.jpeg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/glorious-exploits-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/glorious-exploits-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/glorious-exploits.jpeg 900w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 678px) 100vw, 678px" /></a> Ferdia Lennon, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250893697" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Glorious Exploits</a></em>; cover design by Gregg Kulick (Henry Holt, March)</span>
<p>Hilarious! Brings me joy.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://sross.tumblr.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Stephanie Ross</a></em></p>
<p>This cover could easily have been too silly, but the muted orange, leftward glance, and slightly angry expression create a Goldilocks balance between funny and intriguing.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.bethsteidle.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Beth Steidle</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780771051869" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246525" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/laymans-report/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/laymans-report.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="layman&#8217;s report" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Eugene Marten, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780771051869&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Layman’s Report&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Kate Sinclair (McClelland &#038; Stewart, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/laymans-report-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/laymans-report.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246525" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/laymans-report.jpeg" alt="layman's report" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/laymans-report.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/laymans-report-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/laymans-report-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/laymans-report-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Eugene Marten, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780771051869" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Layman’s Report</a></em>; cover design by Kate Sinclair (McClelland &amp; Stewart, August)</span>
<p>I loved the vintage vibes of this cover, and what fun fonts!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jayanicely.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jaya Nicely</a></em></p>
<p>It feels nostalgic and contemporary at the same time.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.heaeunhan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Grace Han</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593701362" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246519" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/defectors-paola-ramos-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/defectors-paola-ramos-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="671,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="defectors paola ramos copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Paola Ramos, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593701362&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Defectors&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Chantal Jachan (Pantheon, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/defectors-paola-ramos-copy-201x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/defectors-paola-ramos-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246519" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/defectors-paola-ramos-copy.jpg" alt="defectors paola ramos copy" width="671" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/defectors-paola-ramos-copy.jpg 671w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/defectors-paola-ramos-copy-201x300.jpg 201w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/defectors-paola-ramos-copy-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/defectors-paola-ramos-copy-34x50.jpg 34w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px" /></a> Paola Ramos, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593701362" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Defectors</a></em>; cover design by Chantal Jahchan (Pantheon, September)</span>
<p>One of those covers that, after seeing it, you just nod and say “yep, of course” and accept that nothing else could possibly have worked better.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://chasematt.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Matt Chase</a></em></p>
<p>Minimal and impactful!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.heaeunhan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Grace Han</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780525541639" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246587" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/little-rot-uk/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Little-Rot-UK.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1611" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Little-Rot-UK" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Akwaeke Emezi, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780525541639&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Little Rot&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Kishan Rajani (Faber &#038; Faber, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Little-Rot-UK-186x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Little-Rot-UK-636x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246587" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Little-Rot-UK-636x1024.jpg" alt="Little-Rot-UK" width="636" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Little-Rot-UK-636x1024.jpg 636w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Little-Rot-UK-186x300.jpg 186w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Little-Rot-UK-768x1237.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Little-Rot-UK-37x60.jpg 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Little-Rot-UK-953x1536.jpg 953w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Little-Rot-UK-31x50.jpg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Little-Rot-UK.jpg 1000w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 636px) 100vw, 636px" /></a> Akwaeke Emezi, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780525541639" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Little Rot</a></em>; cover design by Kishan Rajani (Faber &amp; Faber, July)</span>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="http://www.ZoeNorvell.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Zoe Norvell</a></em></p>
<p>Zoomed-in, gooey mouth AND brown background! The number of times I’ve been told no to each of these things on their own… and combined! Look at this beauty! Don’t you just want to feel it? Could anyone let me know what finish this has? Lol. Kishan strikes again!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.rachelakedesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Rachel Ake</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374602635" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239022" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/intermezzo/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Intermezzo.jpeg" data-orig-size="652,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Intermezzo" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Sally Rooney, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374602635&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Intermezzo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by June Park and Rodrigo Corral, art by June Park (FSG, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Intermezzo-196x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Intermezzo.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239022" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Intermezzo.jpeg" alt="Intermezzo" width="652" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Intermezzo.jpeg 652w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Intermezzo-196x300.jpeg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Intermezzo-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Intermezzo-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px" /></a> Sally Rooney, <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374602635" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Intermezzo</a></em>; cover design by June Park and Rodrigo Corral, art by June Park (FSG, September)</span>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="http://www.ZoeNorvell.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Zoe Norvell</a></em></p>
<p>It&#8217;s subtle but textured. It&#8217;s a cover that is already beautiful when you pick it up but becomes more brilliant as you get to know the story.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jowoho.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joan Wong</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781957363875" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246520" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/lukebird/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LukeBird.jpg" data-orig-size="963,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Miranda Darling thunderhead" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Miranda Darling, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781957363875&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Thunderhead&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Luke Bird (Scribe, May)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LukeBird-193x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LukeBird-657x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246520" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LukeBird-657x1024.jpg" alt="Miranda Darling thunderhead" width="657" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LukeBird-657x1024.jpg 657w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LukeBird-193x300.jpg 193w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LukeBird-768x1196.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LukeBird-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LukeBird-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/LukeBird.jpg 963w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 657px) 100vw, 657px" /></a> Miranda Darling, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781957363875" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Thunderhead</a></em>; cover design by Luke Bird (Scribe, May)</span>
<p>It&#8217;s the pearls, they&#8217;re floating on a plane between me and the rest of the cover and it is mesmerising.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jacksmyth.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jack Smyth</a></em></p>
<p>So beautiful and strange. I don’t know what’s going on, but I want to.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.laurenpc.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lauren Peters-Collaer</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://peninsulapress.co.uk/products/novices-of-lerna" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="245970" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/attachment/9781913512569/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9781913512569.jpg" data-orig-size="1524,2339" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="9781913512569" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Ángel Bonomini, tr. Jordan Landsman, &lt;em&gt;Novices of Lerna&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jonny Pelham (Peninsula Press, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9781913512569-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9781913512569-667x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-245970" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9781913512569-667x1024.jpg" alt="" width="667" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9781913512569-667x1024.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9781913512569-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9781913512569-768x1179.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9781913512569-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9781913512569-1001x1536.jpg 1001w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9781913512569-1334x2048.jpg 1334w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9781913512569-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/9781913512569.jpg 1524w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Ángel Bonomini, tr. Jordan Landsman, <em>Novices of Lerna</em>; cover design by Jonny Pelham (Peninsula Press, November)</span>
<p>A beautifully simple and elegant cover.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.tometherington.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Tom Etherington</a></em></p>
<p>There’s something so pleasing about the way that this cover can be viewed from almost any angle, and it still works just as well.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.lukebird.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Luke Bird</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602993" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="245703" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/my-men-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/my-men.jpg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="my men" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Victoria Kielland, tr. Damion Searls, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602993&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;My Men&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Adriana Tonello / Rodrigo Corral Studio&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/my-men-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/my-men.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-245703" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/my-men.jpg" alt="" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/my-men.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/my-men-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/my-men-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/my-men-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Victoria Kielland, tr. Damion Searls, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602993" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">My Men</a></em>; cover design by Adriana Tonello / Rodrigo Corral Studio (Astra House, August)</span>
<p>Playful, eerie, and also elegant—a perfect combination.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://sarahschulte.studio/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sarah Schulte</a></em></p>
<p>Strange and unexpected. I like the way the body parts look like hovering, unsettling, abstract thoughts.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.katesinclair.space/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kate Sinclair</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237826" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="245971" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/giannisi-chimera-rgb-1/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Giannisi-Chimera-rgb-1.jpg" data-orig-size="1562,2400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Giannisi &#8211; Chimera &#8211; rgb (1)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Phoebe Giannisi, tr. Brian Sneeden, &lt;em&gt;Chimera&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Pablo Delcan (New Directions, July 9)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Giannisi-Chimera-rgb-1-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Giannisi-Chimera-rgb-1-666x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-245971" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Giannisi-Chimera-rgb-1-666x1024.jpg" alt="" width="666" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Giannisi-Chimera-rgb-1-666x1024.jpg 666w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Giannisi-Chimera-rgb-1-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Giannisi-Chimera-rgb-1-768x1180.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Giannisi-Chimera-rgb-1-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Giannisi-Chimera-rgb-1-1000x1536.jpg 1000w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Giannisi-Chimera-rgb-1-1333x2048.jpg 1333w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Giannisi-Chimera-rgb-1-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Giannisi-Chimera-rgb-1.jpg 1562w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 666px) 100vw, 666px" /></a> Phoebe Giannisi, tr. Brian Sneeden, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237826" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Chimera</a></em>; cover design by Pablo Delcan (New Directions, July)</span>
<p>This stands out so much in a landscape of large lettered, brightly coloured, shouty book covers. Understated, off-kilter and brilliant.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.tometherington.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Tom Etherington</a></em></p>
<p>This cover is pure poetry. I&#8217;m drawn to the marks, their gesture and placement, and intrigued by the mythology of this lyrical ram.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.nataliaolbinski.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Natalia Olbinski</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250835048" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246527" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/susan-lieu-the-manicurists-daughter/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/susan-lieu-the-manicurists-daughter.jpeg" data-orig-size="658,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="susan lieu the manicurist&#8217;s daughter" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Susan Lieu, &lt;em&gt;The Manicurist’s Daughter&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Juliana Lee (Celadon, March)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/susan-lieu-the-manicurists-daughter-197x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/susan-lieu-the-manicurists-daughter.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246527" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/susan-lieu-the-manicurists-daughter.jpeg" alt="susan lieu the manicurist's daughter" width="658" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/susan-lieu-the-manicurists-daughter.jpeg 658w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/susan-lieu-the-manicurists-daughter-197x300.jpeg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/susan-lieu-the-manicurists-daughter-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/susan-lieu-the-manicurists-daughter-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 658px) 100vw, 658px" /></a> Susan Lieu, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250835048" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Manicurist’s Daughter</a></em>; cover design by Juliana Lee (Celadon, March)</span>
<p>This design creates such a sense of place. A universal place that could be anywhere and offers an entry to the story. You can hear the electricity humming.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://laurenharms.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lauren Harms</a></em></p>
<p>THIS book HAD to have THIS design. It&#8217;s perfect.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="http://www.ZoeNorvell.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Zoe Norvell</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802163707" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239523" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/betsy-lerner-shred-sisters/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Betsy-Lerner-Shred-Sisters-.jpeg" data-orig-size="647,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Betsy Lerner, Shred Sisters" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Betsy Lerner, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802163707&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Shred Sisters&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by TK TK (Grove Press, October 1)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Betsy-Lerner-Shred-Sisters--194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Betsy-Lerner-Shred-Sisters-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239523" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Betsy-Lerner-Shred-Sisters-.jpeg" alt="Betsy Lerner, Shred Sisters" width="647" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Betsy-Lerner-Shred-Sisters-.jpeg 647w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Betsy-Lerner-Shred-Sisters--194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Betsy-Lerner-Shred-Sisters--39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Betsy-Lerner-Shred-Sisters--32x50.jpeg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 647px) 100vw, 647px" /></a> Betsy Lerner, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802163707" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Shred Sisters</a></em>; cover design by Amanda Hudson (Grove Press, October 1)</span>
<p>Love this clever collage, really catches the eye.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.hollyovenden.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Holly Ovenden</a></em></p>
<p>This design has stayed on my mind all year. I find it both timeless and totally fresh.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.morgankrehbiel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Morgan Krehbiel</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593317648" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246514" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/healthy-and-safety-design-by-linda-huang-photograph-by-luis-nieto-dickens/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/healthy-and-safety-design-by-linda-huang-photograph-by-luis-nieto-dickens.jpg" data-orig-size="1688,2550" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="health and safety witt" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Emily Witt, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593317648&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Health and Safety&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Linda Huang, photo by Luis Nieto Dickens (Pantheon, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/healthy-and-safety-design-by-linda-huang-photograph-by-luis-nieto-dickens-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/healthy-and-safety-design-by-linda-huang-photograph-by-luis-nieto-dickens-678x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246514" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/healthy-and-safety-design-by-linda-huang-photograph-by-luis-nieto-dickens-678x1024.jpg" alt="health and safety witt" width="678" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/healthy-and-safety-design-by-linda-huang-photograph-by-luis-nieto-dickens-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/healthy-and-safety-design-by-linda-huang-photograph-by-luis-nieto-dickens-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/healthy-and-safety-design-by-linda-huang-photograph-by-luis-nieto-dickens-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/healthy-and-safety-design-by-linda-huang-photograph-by-luis-nieto-dickens-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/healthy-and-safety-design-by-linda-huang-photograph-by-luis-nieto-dickens-1017x1536.jpg 1017w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/healthy-and-safety-design-by-linda-huang-photograph-by-luis-nieto-dickens-1356x2048.jpg 1356w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/healthy-and-safety-design-by-linda-huang-photograph-by-luis-nieto-dickens-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/healthy-and-safety-design-by-linda-huang-photograph-by-luis-nieto-dickens.jpg 1688w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 678px) 100vw, 678px" /></a> Emily Witt, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593317648" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Health and Safety</a></em>; cover design by Linda Huang, photo by Luis Nieto Dickens (Pantheon, September)</span>
<p>This cover is going for a mood and absolutely nails it. The tension is palpable and utterly compelling.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://milanbozic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Milan Božić</a></em></p>
<p>The type makes my eyes work across the cover in a way that echoes a huge semi-full venue, it makes me feel like I&#8217;m there.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jacksmyth.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jack Smyth</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374608187" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="237698" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-14-best-book-covers-of-may/91b9u6w3l-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91B9u6W3L._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="978,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Thomas Grattan, In Tongues; cover design by Alex Merto (MCD, May 21)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Thomas Grattan, In Tongues; cover design by Alex Merto (MCD, May 21)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91B9u6W3L._SL1500_-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91B9u6W3L._SL1500_-668x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-237698 size-large" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91B9u6W3L._SL1500_-668x1024.jpg" alt="Thomas Grattan, In Tongues; cover design by Alex Merto (MCD, May 21)" width="668" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91B9u6W3L._SL1500_-668x1024.jpg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91B9u6W3L._SL1500_-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91B9u6W3L._SL1500_-768x1178.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91B9u6W3L._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91B9u6W3L._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/91B9u6W3L._SL1500_.jpg 978w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 668px) 100vw, 668px" /></a> Thomas Grattan,<em> <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374608187" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">In Tongues</a></em>; cover design by Alex Merto (MCD, May 21)</span>
<p>I want to zoom in twice over.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://arshraziuddin.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Arsh Raziuddin</a></em></p>
<p>I may be biased since this cover uses my favorite shade of pink, but Alex’s Merto’s design hit this one right on the head. Loved this cover as soon as I saw it.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jayanicely.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jaya Nicely</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="245699" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/71zn83oxfml-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/71zn83oxfmL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="932,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Rebecca Ivory, &lt;em&gt;Free Therapy&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Luke Bird (Jonathan Cape, March 14)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Rebecca Ivory, &lt;em&gt;Free Therapy&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Luke Bird (Jonathan Cape, March 14)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/71zn83oxfmL._SL1500_-186x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/71zn83oxfmL._SL1500_-636x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-245699" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/71zn83oxfmL._SL1500_-636x1024.jpg" alt="Rebecca Ivory, &lt;em&gt;Free Therapy&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Luke Bird (Jonathan Cape, March 14) " width="636" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/71zn83oxfmL._SL1500_-636x1024.jpg 636w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/71zn83oxfmL._SL1500_-186x300.jpg 186w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/71zn83oxfmL._SL1500_-768x1236.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/71zn83oxfmL._SL1500_-37x60.jpg 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/71zn83oxfmL._SL1500_-31x50.jpg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/71zn83oxfmL._SL1500_.jpg 932w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 636px) 100vw, 636px" /> Rebecca Ivory, <em>Free Therapy</em>; cover design by Luke Bird (Jonathan Cape, March 14)</span>
<p>This cover is playful, joyous, and confidently simple. The perforated tabs add a fun tactile element, transforming it into a considered and highly covetable object.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kishanrajanidesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kishan Rajani</a></em></p>
<p>A delight!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.hollyovenden.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Holly Ovenden</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593654101" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231399" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/a12iraftiul-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/A12IRaFtiUL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="993,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Rita Bullwinkel, Headshot" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Rita Bullwinkel, &lt;em&gt;Headshot&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Lynn Buckley (Viking, March 12)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/A12IRaFtiUL._SL1500_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/A12IRaFtiUL._SL1500_-678x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231399" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/A12IRaFtiUL._SL1500_-678x1024.jpg" alt="Rita Bullwinkel, Headshot" width="678" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/A12IRaFtiUL._SL1500_-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/A12IRaFtiUL._SL1500_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/A12IRaFtiUL._SL1500_-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/A12IRaFtiUL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/A12IRaFtiUL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/A12IRaFtiUL._SL1500_.jpg 993w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 678px) 100vw, 678px" /></a> Rita Bullwinkel, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593654101" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Headshot</a></em>; cover design by Lynn Buckley (Viking, March 12)</span>
<p>This cover is so striking (no pun intended). The gradients, the texture, the photo, the typeface. Harmonious. Perfect.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://joannemoneill.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joanne O&#8217;Neill</a></em></p>
<p>This has such a lovely combination of the brutal and the beautiful.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.keenandesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jamie Keenan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063330092" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="233674" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-11-best-book-covers-of-february-2/81d6er8uy3l-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/81D6er8uY3L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="663,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Rae Giana Rashad, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063330092&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Blueprint&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Robin Bilardello (Harper, February 13)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Rae Giana Rashad, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063330092&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Blueprint&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Robin Bilardello (Harper, February 13)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/81D6er8uY3L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/81D6er8uY3L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-233674" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/81D6er8uY3L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="Rae Giana Rashad, The Blueprint; cover design by Robin Bilardello (Harper, February 13)" width="663" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/81D6er8uY3L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 663w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/81D6er8uY3L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/81D6er8uY3L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/81D6er8uY3L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 663px) 100vw, 663px" /></a> Rae Giana Rashad, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063330092" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Blueprint</em></a>; cover design by Robin Bilardello (Harper, February 13)</span>
<p>The weaving of the snake and bird between the maze is so powerful, and the tension between the snake&#8217;s tongue and the bird’s eye is a satisfying detail. I love the unique color palette as well.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://joannemoneill.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joanne O&#8217;Neill</a></em></p>
<p>Full disclosure: Robin and I work in the same art department, so I had the privilege to watch this cover evolve into the brilliance that it ended up as. Nonetheless, it’s a magical example of a perfect collage in an unexpected layout. The silver labyrinth works best IRL.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://milanbozic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Milan Božić</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593803974" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246585" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/forest-of-noise-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/forest-of-noise-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="666,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="forest of noise copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Mosab Abu Toha, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593803974&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Forest of Noise&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Arsh Raziuddin (Knopf, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/forest-of-noise-copy-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/forest-of-noise-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246585" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/forest-of-noise-copy.jpg" alt="forest of noise" width="666" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/forest-of-noise-copy.jpg 666w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/forest-of-noise-copy-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/forest-of-noise-copy-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/forest-of-noise-copy-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 666px) 100vw, 666px" /></a> Mosab Abu Toha, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593803974" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Forest of Noise</a></em>; cover design by Arsh Raziuddin (Knopf, October)</span>
<p>One of those covers you <em>feel</em> rather than see; as captivating as the poems inside.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.morgankrehbiel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Morgan Krehbiel</a></em></p>
<p>A beautiful cover, full of emotion.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://epmock.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Eli Mock</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374610784" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231342" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/61dvuhkpufl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/61DvUHkpuFL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="964,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Sheila Heti, Alphabetical Diaries" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Sheila Heti, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374610784&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Alphabetical Diaries&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Na Kim (FSG, February 6)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/61DvUHkpuFL._SL1500_-193x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/61DvUHkpuFL._SL1500_-658x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231342" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/61DvUHkpuFL._SL1500_-658x1024.jpg" alt="Sheila Heti, Alphabetical Diaries" width="658" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/61DvUHkpuFL._SL1500_-658x1024.jpg 658w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/61DvUHkpuFL._SL1500_-193x300.jpg 193w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/61DvUHkpuFL._SL1500_-768x1195.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/61DvUHkpuFL._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/61DvUHkpuFL._SL1500_-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/61DvUHkpuFL._SL1500_.jpg 964w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 658px) 100vw, 658px" /></a> Sheila Heti, <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374610784" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alphabetical Diaries</a></em>; cover design by Na Kim (FSG, February 6)</span>
<p>Of course she did!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://arshraziuddin.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Arsh Raziuddin</a></em></p>
<p>The typographic gymnastics and simple use of color are incredible.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://epmock.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Eli Mock</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593544372" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246806" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/attachment/201102398/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/201102398-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1696,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="colored television" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Danzy Senna, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593544372&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Colored Television&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Lauren Peters-Collaer (Riverhead, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/201102398-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/201102398-678x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246806" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/201102398-678x1024.jpg" alt="colored television" width="678" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/201102398-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/201102398-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/201102398-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/201102398-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/201102398-1017x1536.jpg 1017w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/201102398-1356x2048.jpg 1356w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/201102398-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/201102398-scaled.jpg 1696w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 678px) 100vw, 678px" /></a> Danzy Senna, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593544372" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Colored Television</em></a>; cover design by Lauren Peters-Collaer (Riverhead, September)</span>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.heaeunhan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Grace Han</a></em></p>
<p>This is such a strange colour scheme, but it works so well and there’s something about those two brown dots lining up with the eyes that grabs me.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.keenandesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jamie Keenan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593654828" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231363" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/91uvjfwayl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91uVJFWayL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="994,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Phillip B. Williams, Ours" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Phillip B. Williams, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593654828&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ours&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Lynn Buckley; art by Damilola Opedun (Viking, February 20)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91uVJFWayL._SL1500_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91uVJFWayL._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231363" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91uVJFWayL._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg" alt="Phillip B. Williams, Ours" width="679" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91uVJFWayL._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg 679w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91uVJFWayL._SL1500_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91uVJFWayL._SL1500_-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91uVJFWayL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91uVJFWayL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91uVJFWayL._SL1500_.jpg 994w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px" /></a> Phillip B. Williams, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593654828" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Ours</em></a>; cover design by Lynn Buckley; art by Damilola Opedun (Viking, February)</span>
<p>A more perfect painting for this book doesn&#8217;t exist. The attitude the painting exudes, the cropping, the nods to renaissance painting but with Black subjects. It&#8217;s just perfect.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jennisurasky.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jenni Surasky</a></em></p>
<p>The cropping of the painting and handlettered type—the emotional pull of this jacket is undeniable.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.alisonforner.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alison Forner</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246649" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/mood-swings_katesinclair/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mood-Swings_KateSinclair.jpg" data-orig-size="624,972" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Mood-Swings_KateSinclair" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Frankie Barnet, &lt;em&gt;Mood Swings&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Kate Sinclair (McLelland &#038; Stewart, May)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mood-Swings_KateSinclair-193x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mood-Swings_KateSinclair.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246649" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mood-Swings_KateSinclair.jpg" alt="" width="624" height="972" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mood-Swings_KateSinclair.jpg 624w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mood-Swings_KateSinclair-193x300.jpg 193w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mood-Swings_KateSinclair-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Mood-Swings_KateSinclair-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 624px) 100vw, 624px" /> Frankie Barnet, <em>Mood Swings</em>; cover design by Kate Sinclair (McLelland &amp; Stewart, May)</span>
<p>Give me a dog on a cover any day! Kate is a master at using retro imagery with unique type. See also her cover for<em> Layman’s Report</em>. Also love the US cover (by Rodrigo Corral). <em>[ed note: both also on this list!]</em> After seeing the two, I knew I NEEDED to read this book and what more is this job?</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.rachelakedesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Rachel Ake</a></em></p>
<p>Missing Faces seems to be a thing at the moment, one of those bursts of design weather under no one’s control, but this one still deeply tickles my fancy.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593701607" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246603" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/nicked/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/nicked.jpeg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="nicked" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;M.T. Anderson, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593701607&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Nicked&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Zak Tebbal (Pantheon, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/nicked-199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/nicked.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246603" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/nicked.jpeg" alt="nicked" width="662" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/nicked.jpeg 662w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/nicked-199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/nicked-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/nicked-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px" /></a> M.T. Anderson, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593701607" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Nicked</a></em>; cover design by Zak Tebbal (Pantheon, July)</span>
<p>Playfully medieval with gorgeous typography.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://epmock.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Eli Mock</a></em></p>
<p>My role at Bindery Books has thrust me into the world of fantasy and noir fiction. It’s thrilling to turn the fantasy cover trope on its skull (!) as the designer of <em>Nicked</em> has. I applaud the simplicity of the thief’s brazen gesture, gripping the fearful half skull through its non-weeping socket; it illustrates M. T. Anderson’s title artfully.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://charlottestrick.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Charlotte Strick</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593730249" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231438" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/71dhm6zwcul-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71dHm6zWCUL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Salman Rushdie, Knife" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Salman Rushdie, &lt;em&gt;Knife&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Arsh Raziuddin (Random House, April)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71dHm6zWCUL._SL1500_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71dHm6zWCUL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231438" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71dHm6zWCUL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" alt="Salman Rushdie, Knife" width="683" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71dHm6zWCUL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71dHm6zWCUL._SL1500_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71dHm6zWCUL._SL1500_-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71dHm6zWCUL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71dHm6zWCUL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71dHm6zWCUL._SL1500_.jpg 1000w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></a> Salman Rushdie, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593730249" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Knife</a></em>; cover design by Arsh Raziuddin (Random House, April)</span>
<p>Brilliant, striking. Serene despite the violence of the knife wound. I can&#8217;t imagine a more perfect cover for this book.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.nataliaolbinski.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Natalia Olbinski</a></em></p>
<p>Such a fitting solution that it feels impossible to imagine this book having any other cover.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://aliciatatone.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alicia Tatone</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246595" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/81xmsswddyl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81xMssWDdyL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1023,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Jenny Heijun Wills, &lt;em&gt;Everything and Nothing at All&lt;/em&gt;; design by Terri Nimmo (Knopf Canada, August)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Jenny Heijun Wills, &lt;em&gt;Everything and Nothing at All&lt;/em&gt;; design by Terri Nimmo (Knopf Canada, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81xMssWDdyL._SL1500_-205x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81xMssWDdyL._SL1500_-698x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246595" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81xMssWDdyL._SL1500_-698x1024.jpg" alt="Jenny Heijun Wills, &lt;em&gt;Everything and Nothing at All&lt;/em&gt;; design by Terri Nimmo (Knopf Canada, August) " width="698" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81xMssWDdyL._SL1500_-698x1024.jpg 698w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81xMssWDdyL._SL1500_-205x300.jpg 205w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81xMssWDdyL._SL1500_-768x1126.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81xMssWDdyL._SL1500_-41x60.jpg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81xMssWDdyL._SL1500_-34x50.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81xMssWDdyL._SL1500_.jpg 1023w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 698px) 100vw, 698px" /> Jenny Heijun Wills, <em>Everything and Nothing at All</em>; design by Terri Nimmo (Knopf Canada, August)</span>
<p>So weird and yet so beautifully balanced. “Essays” is the star of the show.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.lukebird.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Luke Bird</a></em></p>
<p>This somehow combines joy and uneasiness, and in such a beautiful way!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.mathmonahan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Math Monahan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811231534" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246807" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/herscht-07769-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Herscht-07769.avif" data-orig-size="1000,1600" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Herscht 07769" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Laszlo Krasznahorkai, tr. Ottilie Mulzet, &lt;em&gt;Herscht 07769&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Paul Sahre / O.O.P.S. (New Directions, September)&lt;/p&gt;
