<p>Great marriage (couldn&#8217;t resist&#8230;) of illustration and typography.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/jennycarrow_covers/?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jenny Carrow</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246732" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/mcglue-uk-cover/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/mcglue-uk-cover.jpeg" data-orig-size="976,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="mcglue uk cover" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Ottessa Moshfegh, &lt;em&gt;McGlue&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jonathan Pelham (Jonathan Cape, March)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/mcglue-uk-cover-195x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/mcglue-uk-cover-666x1024.jpeg" class="size-large wp-image-246732" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/mcglue-uk-cover-666x1024.jpeg" alt="mcglue uk cover" width="666" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/mcglue-uk-cover-666x1024.jpeg 666w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/mcglue-uk-cover-195x300.jpeg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/mcglue-uk-cover-768x1180.jpeg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/mcglue-uk-cover-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/mcglue-uk-cover-33x50.jpeg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/mcglue-uk-cover.jpeg 976w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 666px) 100vw, 666px" /> Ottessa Moshfegh, <em>McGlue</em>; cover design by Jonathan Pelham (Jonathan Cape, March)</span>
<p>The tension between the angular typography and the lush painting, the fantastic use of negative space, and the mystery of what lies outside the frame—this one is a stunner.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.devingrosz.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Devin Grosz</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781964098005" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246691" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/trouble-in-censorville/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Trouble-in-Censorville.jpeg" data-orig-size="668,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Trouble in Censorville" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Nadine M. Kalin and Rebekah Modrak, eds., &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781964098005&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Trouble in Censorville&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Ben Denzer (Disobedience Press, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Trouble-in-Censorville-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Trouble-in-Censorville.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246691" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Trouble-in-Censorville.jpeg" alt="Trouble in Censorville" width="668" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Trouble-in-Censorville.jpeg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Trouble-in-Censorville-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Trouble-in-Censorville-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Trouble-in-Censorville-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 668px) 100vw, 668px" /></a> Nadine M. Kalin and Rebekah Modrak, eds., <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781964098005" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Trouble in Censorville</a></em>; cover design by Ben Denzer (Disobedience Press, July)</span>
<p>So smart.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.heaeunhan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Grace Han</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143137900" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246714" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/the-last-man/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-last-man.jpeg" data-orig-size="653,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="the last man" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Mary Shelley, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143137900&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Last Man&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design and illustration by Eleanor Taylor (Penguin Classics, April)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-last-man-196x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-last-man.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246714" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-last-man.jpeg" alt="the last man" width="653" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-last-man.jpeg 653w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-last-man-196x300.jpeg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-last-man-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-last-man-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 653px) 100vw, 653px" /></a> Mary Shelley, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780143137900" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Last Man</a></em>; illustration by Eleanor Taylor, art direction by Elizabeth Yaffe (Penguin Classics, April)</span>
<p>Eleanor&#8217;s illustration integrates and breaks through the classic series design format adding dimension, lushness and a provocative peek into &#8220;a world where newly-forged communities and reverence for nature rise from the ashes of a pandemic-ravaged society&#8221; in this climate action fiction. Perfect in concept and execution.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.nicolecaputo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Nicole Caputo</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246598" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/1984-sweden/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1984-sweden.jpg" data-orig-size="1642,2539" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="1984 sweden" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;George Orwell, tr. Ragnar Strömberg, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.modernista.se/bocker/1984-1&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;1984&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Rasmus Pettersson (Modernista, March)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1984-sweden-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1984-sweden-662x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246598" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1984-sweden-662x1024.jpg" alt="1984 sweden" width="662" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1984-sweden-662x1024.jpg 662w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1984-sweden-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1984-sweden-768x1188.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1984-sweden-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1984-sweden-993x1536.jpg 993w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1984-sweden-1324x2048.jpg 1324w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1984-sweden-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1984-sweden.jpg 1642w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px" /> George Orwell, tr. Ragnar Strömberg, <em><a href="https://www.modernista.se/bocker/1984-1" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">1984</a></em>; cover design by Rasmus Pettersson (Modernista, March)</span>
<p>Everything Rasmus Pettersson does is brilliant. This Swedish edition of <em>1984</em> is not only gorgeous but manages to resist the usual Orwellian tropes.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://albanfischerdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alban Fischer</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374611613" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="242056" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/dear-dickhead/attachment/9780374611620/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/9780374611620.jpg" data-orig-size="1613,2475" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="dear dickhead" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Virginie Despentes, tr. Frank Wynne, &lt;em&gt;Dear Dickhead&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Alex Merto (FSG, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/9780374611620-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/9780374611620-667x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-242056" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/9780374611620-667x1024.jpg" alt="dear dickhead" width="667" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/9780374611620-667x1024.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/9780374611620-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/9780374611620-768x1178.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/9780374611620-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/9780374611620-1001x1536.jpg 1001w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/9780374611620-1335x2048.jpg 1335w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/9780374611620-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/9780374611620.jpg 1613w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Virginie Despentes, tr. Frank Wynne, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374611613" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Dear Dickhead</a></em>; cover design by Alex Merto (FSG, September)</span>
<p>Perfect.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.laurenpc.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lauren Peters-Collaer</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798218471163" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246593" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/schroeder-cassidy-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/schroeder-cassidy-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="625,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="schroeder cassidy copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Neal Cassidy, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798218471163&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Schroeder&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jamie Keenan (M&#038;S Publishing, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/schroeder-cassidy-copy-188x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/schroeder-cassidy-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246593" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/schroeder-cassidy-copy.jpg" alt="schroeder cassidy copy" width="625" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/schroeder-cassidy-copy.jpg 625w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/schroeder-cassidy-copy-188x300.jpg 188w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/schroeder-cassidy-copy-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/schroeder-cassidy-copy-31x50.jpg 31w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 625px) 100vw, 625px" /></a> Neal Cassidy, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798218471163" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Schroeder</a></em>; cover design by Jamie Keenan (M&amp;S Publishing, October)</span>
<p>That author type is so, <em>so</em> good. Every element is just really creepy. In a good way.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.lukebird.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Luke Bird</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781644453094" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246590" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/hold-everything/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/hold-everything.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="hold everything" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Dobby Gibson, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781644453094&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Hold Everything&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Alban Fischer (Graywolf, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/hold-everything-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/hold-everything.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246590" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/hold-everything.jpeg" alt="hold everything" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/hold-everything.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/hold-everything-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/hold-everything-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/hold-everything-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Dobby Gibson, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781644453094" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Hold Everything</a></em>; cover design by Alban Fischer (Graywolf, October)</span>
<p>So simple but so impactful. I love how the illustration feels at once otherworldly and familiar.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://dana-li.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Dana Li</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662522611" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="243325" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-16-best-book-covers-of-september/81ayev5c6yl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/81AyEV5C6YL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="971,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Bryan VanDyke, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662522611&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;In Our Likeness&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Joanne O&#8217;Neill (Little A, September 1)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Bryan VanDyke, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662522611&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;In Our Likeness&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Joanne O&#8217;Neill (Little A, September )&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/81AyEV5C6YL._SL1500_-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/81AyEV5C6YL._SL1500_-663x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-243325" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/81AyEV5C6YL._SL1500_-663x1024.jpg" alt="Bryan VanDyke, In Our Likeness; cover design by Joanne O'Neill (Little A, September 1)" width="663" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/81AyEV5C6YL._SL1500_-663x1024.jpg 663w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/81AyEV5C6YL._SL1500_-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/81AyEV5C6YL._SL1500_-768x1186.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/81AyEV5C6YL._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/81AyEV5C6YL._SL1500_-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/81AyEV5C6YL._SL1500_.jpg 971w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 663px) 100vw, 663px" /></a> Bryan VanDyke, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662522611" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">In Our Likeness</a></em>; cover design by Joanne O&#8217;Neill (Little A, September)</span>
<p>Brilliant! Chef’s kiss! Immediately understood what might be under this cover and so beautiful. That tension between the hot pink splotches and the sparkle has me hooked.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.rachelakedesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Rachel Ake</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063286870" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246733" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/rainbow-black-maggie-thrash/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rainbow-black-maggie-thrash.jpeg" data-orig-size="664,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="rainbow black maggie thrash" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;(Harper Perennial, March)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rainbow-black-maggie-thrash-199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rainbow-black-maggie-thrash.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246733" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rainbow-black-maggie-thrash.jpeg" alt="" width="664" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rainbow-black-maggie-thrash.jpeg 664w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rainbow-black-maggie-thrash-199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rainbow-black-maggie-thrash-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rainbow-black-maggie-thrash-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 664px) 100vw, 664px" /></a> Maggie Thrash, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063286870" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Rainbow Black</a></em>; cover design by Joanne O&#8217;Neill (Harper Perennial, March)</span>
<p>I remember the ‘90s Satanic Panic from my adolescence, and this cover is a fantastic modern spin on that wild cultural flashpoint. I especially like the type treatment—the edges of the type vibrate, as if they had been repeatedly run through a Xerox machine.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.devingrosz.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Devin Grosz</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238632" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246735" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/liontaming-in-america-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/liontaming-in-america-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="647,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="liontaming in america copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Elizabeth Willis, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238632&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Liontaming in America&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Joan Wong (New Directions, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/liontaming-in-america-copy-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/liontaming-in-america-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246735" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/liontaming-in-america-copy.jpg" alt="liontaming in america copy" width="647" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/liontaming-in-america-copy.jpg 647w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/liontaming-in-america-copy-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/liontaming-in-america-copy-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/liontaming-in-america-copy-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 647px) 100vw, 647px" /></a> Elizabeth Willis, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238632" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Liontaming in America</a></em>; cover design by Joan Wong (New Directions, September)</span>
<p>I have to limit myself to one Joan Wong every year, so I’m choosing this one, though I could easily pick <em>The Obscene Bird of Night</em> for the melty dreamworld nightmare goodness. Anyway. The lion, perched, folded into the loop. The mountain, nestled, in another. I’m in.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781958417492" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246584" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/sicily-my-swet/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sicily-my-swet.jpeg" data-orig-size="754,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="sicily my swet" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Victorian Granof, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781958417492&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Sicily, My Sweet&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Evi-O Studio (Hardie Grant Books, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sicily-my-swet-226x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sicily-my-swet.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246584" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sicily-my-swet.jpeg" alt="sicily my swet" width="754" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sicily-my-swet.jpeg 754w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sicily-my-swet-226x300.jpeg 226w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sicily-my-swet-45x60.jpeg 45w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/sicily-my-swet-38x50.jpeg 38w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 754px) 100vw, 754px" /></a> Victorian Granof, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781958417492" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sicily, My Sweet</a></em>; cover design by Evi-O Studio (Hardie Grant Books, October)</span>
<p>This design is both extravagant and stunningly simple. A dessert itself.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.morgankrehbiel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Morgan Krehbiel</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602856" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246540" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/71w17voakol-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71W17VoAkOL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1071,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="berlin atomized" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Julia Kornberg, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602856&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Berlin Atomized&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Erik Carter (Astra House, December)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71W17VoAkOL._SL1500_-214x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71W17VoAkOL._SL1500_-731x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246540" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71W17VoAkOL._SL1500_-731x1024.jpg" alt="berlin atomized" width="731" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71W17VoAkOL._SL1500_-731x1024.jpg 731w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71W17VoAkOL._SL1500_-214x300.jpg 214w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71W17VoAkOL._SL1500_-768x1076.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71W17VoAkOL._SL1500_-43x60.jpg 43w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71W17VoAkOL._SL1500_-36x50.jpg 36w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71W17VoAkOL._SL1500_.jpg 1071w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 731px) 100vw, 731px" /></a> Julia Kornberg, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602856" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Berlin Atomized</a></em>; cover design by Erik Carter (Astra House, December)</span>
<p>Pure energy exploding craziness but at the same time super controlled and refined.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://bendenzer.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Ben Denzer</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374609849" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231360" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/617bczxxxbl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/617BCZxxxbL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1031,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Sloane Crosley, Grief is for People" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Sloane Crosley, &lt;em&gt;Grief is for People&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Alex Merto (MCD, February)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/617BCZxxxbL._SL1500_-206x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/617BCZxxxbL._SL1500_-704x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231360" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/617BCZxxxbL._SL1500_-704x1024.jpg" alt="Sloane Crosley, Grief is for People" width="704" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/617BCZxxxbL._SL1500_-704x1024.jpg 704w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/617BCZxxxbL._SL1500_-206x300.jpg 206w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/617BCZxxxbL._SL1500_-768x1117.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/617BCZxxxbL._SL1500_-41x60.jpg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/617BCZxxxbL._SL1500_-34x50.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/617BCZxxxbL._SL1500_.jpg 1031w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px" /></a> Sloane Crosley, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374609849" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Grief is for People</a></em>; cover design by Alex Merto (MCD, February)</span>
<p>Typographic perfection.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316374880" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246582" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/81u6wfukgdl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81U6WfUKGDL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="932,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="splinters uk" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Leslie Jamison, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316374880&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Splinters&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jack Smyth (Granta Books, February)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81U6WfUKGDL._SL1500_-186x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81U6WfUKGDL._SL1500_-636x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246582" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81U6WfUKGDL._SL1500_-636x1024.jpg" alt="splinters uk" width="636" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81U6WfUKGDL._SL1500_-636x1024.jpg 636w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81U6WfUKGDL._SL1500_-186x300.jpg 186w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81U6WfUKGDL._SL1500_-768x1236.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81U6WfUKGDL._SL1500_-37x60.jpg 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81U6WfUKGDL._SL1500_-31x50.jpg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81U6WfUKGDL._SL1500_.jpg 932w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 636px) 100vw, 636px" /></a> Leslie Jamison, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316374880" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Splinters</a></em>; cover design by Jack Smyth (Granta Books, February)</span>
<p>I ordered this book immediately after seeing the cover Jack posted. Woah it’s so good, it feels broken.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/robinbillz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Robin Bilardello</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374605896" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246523" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/any-person-is-the-only-self-elisa-gabbert/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/any-person-is-the-only-self-elisa-gabbert.jpeg" data-orig-size="652,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="any person is the only self elisa gabbert" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Elisa Gabbert, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374605896&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Any Person is the Only Self&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by June Park (FSG Originals, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/any-person-is-the-only-self-elisa-gabbert-196x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/any-person-is-the-only-self-elisa-gabbert.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246523" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/any-person-is-the-only-self-elisa-gabbert.jpeg" alt="any person is the only self elisa gabbert" width="652" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/any-person-is-the-only-self-elisa-gabbert.jpeg 652w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/any-person-is-the-only-self-elisa-gabbert-196x300.jpeg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/any-person-is-the-only-self-elisa-gabbert-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/any-person-is-the-only-self-elisa-gabbert-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px" /></a> Elisa Gabbert, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374605896" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Any Person is the Only Self</a></em>; cover design by June Park (FSG Originals, June)</span>
<p>I’m a sucker for a painting on a cover and this beautiful, almost monochrome piece by Jess Allen works so wonderfully with June Park’s minimal design. Adding that red stripe is also genius.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jayanicely.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jaya Nicely</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781517917234" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246808" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/attachment/195668137/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/195668137.jpg" data-orig-size="1688,2475" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="prairie edge" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Conor Kerr, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781517917234&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Prairie Edge&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Kate Sinclair (University of Minnesota Press, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/195668137-205x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/195668137-698x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246808" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/195668137-698x1024.jpg" alt="prairie edge" width="698" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/195668137-698x1024.jpg 698w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/195668137-205x300.jpg 205w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/195668137-768x1126.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/195668137-41x60.jpg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/195668137-1048x1536.jpg 1048w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/195668137-1397x2048.jpg 1397w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/195668137-34x50.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/195668137.jpg 1688w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 698px) 100vw, 698px" /></a> Conor Kerr, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781517917234" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Prairie Edge</a></em>; cover design by Kate Sinclair (University of Minnesota Press, June)</span>
<p>This design reminds me of looking out of an airplane window, but instead of seeing something distant and expected, it is too close and too monstrous. The claustrophobia and minimalism work perfectly in concert.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.bethsteidle.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Beth Steidle</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593449097" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246652" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/81-rupz6qul-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81-rupz6qUL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="964,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Karla Cornejo Villavicencio, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593449097&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Catalina&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Grace Han (One World, July)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Karla Cornejo Villavicencio, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593449097&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Catalina&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Grace Han (One World, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81-rupz6qUL._SL1500_-193x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81-rupz6qUL._SL1500_-658x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246652" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81-rupz6qUL._SL1500_-658x1024.jpg" alt="Karla Cornejo Villavicencio, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593449097&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Catalina&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Grace Han (One World, July)" width="658" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81-rupz6qUL._SL1500_-658x1024.jpg 658w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81-rupz6qUL._SL1500_-193x300.jpg 193w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81-rupz6qUL._SL1500_-768x1195.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81-rupz6qUL._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81-rupz6qUL._SL1500_-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81-rupz6qUL._SL1500_.jpg 964w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 658px) 100vw, 658px" /></a> Karla Cornejo Villavicencio, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593449097" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Catalina</a></em>; cover design by Grace Han (One World, July)</span>
<p>It has a 1920s elegance that is timeless but is also ethereal in a way that is very contemporary.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.vivianrowe.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Vivian Lopez Rowe</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593316085" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246529" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/819ycgclrml-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/819ycGCLRML._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="940,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Mina’s Matchbox uk" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Yoko Ogawa, tr. Stephen Snyder, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593316085&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Mina’s Matchbox&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Suzanne Dean, illustration by Gerard Dubois (Harvill Secker, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/819ycGCLRML._SL1500_-188x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/819ycGCLRML._SL1500_-642x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246529" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/819ycGCLRML._SL1500_-642x1024.jpg" alt="Mina’s Matchbox uk" width="642" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/819ycGCLRML._SL1500_-642x1024.jpg 642w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/819ycGCLRML._SL1500_-188x300.jpg 188w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/819ycGCLRML._SL1500_-768x1226.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/819ycGCLRML._SL1500_-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/819ycGCLRML._SL1500_-31x50.jpg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/819ycGCLRML._SL1500_.jpg 940w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 642px) 100vw, 642px" /></a> Yoko Ogawa, tr. Stephen Snyder, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593316085" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mina’s Matchbox</a></em>; cover design by Suzanne Dean, illustration by Gerard Dubois (Harvill Secker, August)</span>
<p>Suzanne is a master of using the perfect illustrator for a cover.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://annamorrison.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Anna Morrison</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593438923" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246526" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/it-had-to-be-you/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/it-had-to-be-you.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="it had to be you" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Eliza Jane Brazier, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593438923&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;It Had to Be You&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Emily Osborne, art by Avinash Weersekera (Berkley, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/it-had-to-be-you-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/it-had-to-be-you.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246526" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/it-had-to-be-you.jpeg" alt="" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/it-had-to-be-you.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/it-had-to-be-you-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/it-had-to-be-you-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/it-had-to-be-you-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Eliza Jane Brazier, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593438923" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">It Had to Be You</a></em>; cover design by Emily Osborne, art by Avinash Weersekera (Berkley, July)</span>
<p>The colors caught my eye immediately. A great twist on two genre styles, hitting the perfect tone. Suspenseful but bright and contemporary.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://laurenharms.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lauren Harms</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780226825977" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246736" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/the-specter-of-the-archive/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Specter-of-the-Archive.jpeg" data-orig-size="658,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="The Specter of the Archive" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Nicholas Popper, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780226825977&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Specter of the Archive&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Elisha Zepeda (University of Chicago Press, January)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Specter-of-the-Archive-197x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Specter-of-the-Archive.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246736" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Specter-of-the-Archive.jpeg" alt="The Specter of the Archive" width="658" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Specter-of-the-Archive.jpeg 658w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Specter-of-the-Archive-197x300.jpeg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Specter-of-the-Archive-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Specter-of-the-Archive-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 658px) 100vw, 658px" /></a> Nicholas Popper, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780226825977" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Specter of the Archive</a></em>; cover design by Elisha Zepeda (University of Chicago Press, January)</span>
<p>Delicious.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063343535" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246758" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/81xg5jizpql-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81XG5JIZPqL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="987,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="women&#8217;s hotel" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Daniel M. Lavery, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063343535&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Women&#8217;s Hotel&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Stephen Brayda, art by Thibaud Herem (Harpervia, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81XG5JIZPqL._SL1500_-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81XG5JIZPqL._SL1500_-674x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246758" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81XG5JIZPqL._SL1500_-674x1024.jpg" alt="women's hotel" width="674" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81XG5JIZPqL._SL1500_-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81XG5JIZPqL._SL1500_-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81XG5JIZPqL._SL1500_-768x1167.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81XG5JIZPqL._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81XG5JIZPqL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81XG5JIZPqL._SL1500_.jpg 987w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px" /></a> Daniel M. Lavery, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063343535" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Women&#8217;s Hotel</a></em>; cover design by Stephen Brayda, art by Thibaud Herem (Harpervia, October)</span>
<p>Love the delicate details in the windows.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/jennycarrow_covers/?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jenny Carrow</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237970" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246599" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/tablets-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Tablets-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Tablets copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Dunya Mikhail, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237970&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Tablets: Secrets of the Clay&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Janet Hansen (New Directions, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Tablets-copy-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Tablets-copy-683x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246599" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Tablets-copy-683x1024.jpg" alt="Tablets copy" width="683" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Tablets-copy-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Tablets-copy-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Tablets-copy-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Tablets-copy-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Tablets-copy-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Tablets-copy.jpg 1000w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></a> Dunya Mikhail, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237970" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Tablets: Secrets of the Clay</a></em>; cover design by Janet Hansen (New Directions, September)</span>
<p>The collage of the author&#8217;s artwork lends an element of the archival while the small scrap of paper itself is suggestive of a tablet. Beautifully chaotic and considered.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://albanfischerdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alban Fischer</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593535844" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="243340" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-16-best-book-covers-of-september/817flx43avl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/817fLx43AVL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Abi Maxwell, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593535844&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;One Day I’ll Grow Up and Be a Beautiful Woman: A Mother’s Story&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Janet Hansen (Knopf, September 17)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Abi Maxwell, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593535844&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;One Day I’ll Grow Up and Be a Beautiful Woman: A Mother’s Story&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Janet Hansen (Knopf, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/817fLx43AVL._SL1500_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/817fLx43AVL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-243340" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/817fLx43AVL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" alt="Abi Maxwell, One Day I’ll Grow Up and Be a Beautiful Woman: A Mother’s Story; cover design by Janet Hansen (Knopf, September 17)" width="683" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/817fLx43AVL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/817fLx43AVL._SL1500_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/817fLx43AVL._SL1500_-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/817fLx43AVL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/817fLx43AVL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/817fLx43AVL._SL1500_.jpg 1000w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></a> Abi Maxwell, <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593535844" target="_blank" rel="noopener">One Day I’ll Grow Up and Be a Beautiful Woman: A Mother’s Story</a></em>; cover design by Janet Hansen (Knopf, September)</span>
<p>The feeling is that of a whole universe of competing sentiments—fragility/confidence, hope/reality, motherhood/childhood—forced into some kind of haphazard, contingent resolution. There’s a terrific sophistication at work here.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://chasematt.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Matt Chase</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781517908942" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246515" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/attachment/9781517908942/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9781517908942.avif" data-orig-size="596,894" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="helene uri clearing out" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Helene Uri, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781517908942&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Clearing Out&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sarah Schulte (University of Minnesota Press, November) &lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9781517908942-200x300.avif" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9781517908942.avif" class="size-full wp-image-246515" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9781517908942.avif" alt="helene uri clearing out" width="596" height="894" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9781517908942.avif 596w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9781517908942-200x300.avif 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9781517908942-40x60.avif 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/9781517908942-33x50.avif 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 596px) 100vw, 596px" /></a> Helene Uri, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781517908942" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Clearing Out</a></em>; cover design by Sarah Schulte (University of Minnesota Press, November)</span>
<p>I admire Sarah Schulte’s designs. This cover is a lovely example of her artistry and understated elegance.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kelly-winton.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kelly Winton</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063236400" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246458" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/71xakogtzyl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71XaKogtzYL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="981,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="butter uk" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Asako Yuzuki, tr. Polly Barton, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063236400&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Butter&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Emma Pidsley (4th Estate, February 29)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71XaKogtzYL._SL1500_-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71XaKogtzYL._SL1500_-670x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246458" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71XaKogtzYL._SL1500_-670x1024.jpg" alt="butter uk" width="670" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71XaKogtzYL._SL1500_-670x1024.jpg 670w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71XaKogtzYL._SL1500_-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71XaKogtzYL._SL1500_-768x1174.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71XaKogtzYL._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71XaKogtzYL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71XaKogtzYL._SL1500_.jpg 981w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 670px) 100vw, 670px" /></a> Asako Yuzuki, tr. Polly Barton, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063236400" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Butter</a></em>; cover design by Emma Pidsley (4th Estate, February)</span>
<p>I love how unapologetically fun this cover is. The design absolutely sits within the crime genre market but done so in a way we&#8217;ve not seen before. I think a part of why this book has done so well is undeniably in credit to this gorgeous cover.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kishanrajanidesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kishan Rajani</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238533" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="245701" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/erpenbeck_kairos_cover/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/erpenbeck_kairos_cover.jpg" data-orig-size="1617,2400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="erpenbeck_kairos_cover" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Jenny Erpenbeck, tr. Michael Hofmann, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238533&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Kairos&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt; (paperback cover); design by John Gall, illustration by Tina Berning (New Directions, May 14)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/erpenbeck_kairos_cover-202x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/erpenbeck_kairos_cover-690x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-245701" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/erpenbeck_kairos_cover-690x1024.jpg" alt="Jenny Erpenbeck, tr. Michael Hofmann, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238533&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Kairos&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt; (paperback cover); design by John Gall, illustration by Tina Berning (New Directions, May 14) " width="690" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/erpenbeck_kairos_cover-690x1024.jpg 690w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/erpenbeck_kairos_cover-202x300.jpg 202w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/erpenbeck_kairos_cover-768x1140.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/erpenbeck_kairos_cover-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/erpenbeck_kairos_cover-1035x1536.jpg 1035w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/erpenbeck_kairos_cover-1380x2048.jpg 1380w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/erpenbeck_kairos_cover-34x50.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/erpenbeck_kairos_cover.jpg 1617w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px" /></a> Jenny Erpenbeck, tr. Michael Hofmann, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238533" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kairos</a></em> (paperback cover); design by John Gall, illustration by Tina Berning (New Directions, May)</span>
<p>Quietly beautiful and haunting. I love the tension created by the placement of the title.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://sarahschulte.studio/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sarah Schulte</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602597" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="237695" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-14-best-book-covers-of-may/71rgb1hy2l-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/71Rgb1hY2L._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Frankie Barnet, Mood Swings; cover design by Rodrigo Corral (Astra House, May 21)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Frankie Barnet, Mood Swings; cover design by Rodrigo Corral (Astra House, May 21)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/71Rgb1hY2L._SL1500_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/71Rgb1hY2L._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-237695" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/71Rgb1hY2L._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" alt="Frankie Barnet, Mood Swings; cover design by Rodrigo Corral (Astra House, May 21)" width="683" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/71Rgb1hY2L._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/71Rgb1hY2L._SL1500_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/71Rgb1hY2L._SL1500_-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/71Rgb1hY2L._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/71Rgb1hY2L._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/71Rgb1hY2L._SL1500_.jpg 1000w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></a> Frankie Barnet, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602597" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mood Swings</a></em>; cover design by Rodrigo Corral (Astra House, May)</span>
<p>There’s nothing like it out there. Love, love, love.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.vivianrowe.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Vivian Lopez Rowe</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593688960" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246737" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/giovannis-room-8/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/giovannis-room.jpg" data-orig-size="973,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="giovanni&#8217;s room" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;James Baldwin, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593688960&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Giovanni’s Room&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt; (Deluxe Edition); cover design by Megan Wilson, art by Beauford Delaney (Vintage, June)&lt;/p&gt;
