<p>I love the choice to arch the type and sharp serif!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.casandragonzales.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Cassie Gonzales Vu</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781952119859" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246619" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/kayfabe-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/kayfabe-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="697,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="kayfabe copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Chris Koslowski, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781952119859&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Kayfabe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; Hack Barlow cover painting by Brent Engstrom, action figure illustration by Jordan Speer, cover lettering by Kyle Letendre (McSweeney&#8217;s, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/kayfabe-copy-209x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/kayfabe-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246619" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/kayfabe-copy.jpg" alt="kayfabe copy" width="697" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/kayfabe-copy.jpg 697w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/kayfabe-copy-209x300.jpg 209w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/kayfabe-copy-42x60.jpg 42w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/kayfabe-copy-35x50.jpg 35w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 697px) 100vw, 697px" /></a> Chris Koslowski, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781952119859" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kayfabe</a></em>; Hack Barlow cover painting by Brent Engstrom, action figure illustration by Jordan Speer, cover lettering by Kyle Letendre (McSweeney&#8217;s, August)</span>
<p>This is my most favorite cover of the year. The cover looks like actual action figure packaging, and the special effects are just the cherry on top.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.laywankwan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Laywan Kwan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781524747909" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231494" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/91ihcjimfl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91iHcjIMFL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="993,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Porochista Khakpour, Tehrangeles" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Porochista Khakpour, &lt;em&gt;Tehrangele&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Philip (Pantheon, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91iHcjIMFL._SL1500_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91iHcjIMFL._SL1500_-678x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231494" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91iHcjIMFL._SL1500_-678x1024.jpg" alt="Porochista Khakpour, Tehrangeles" width="678" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91iHcjIMFL._SL1500_-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91iHcjIMFL._SL1500_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91iHcjIMFL._SL1500_-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91iHcjIMFL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91iHcjIMFL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/91iHcjIMFL._SL1500_.jpg 993w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 678px) 100vw, 678px" /></a> Porochista Khakpour, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781524747909" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Tehrangeles</a></em>; cover design by Philip Pascuzzo (Pantheon, June)</span>
<p>A little bonkers and completely original.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/jennycarrow_covers/?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jenny Carrow</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238052" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246592" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/the-life-of-tufu/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Life-of-Tufu.jpeg" data-orig-size="621,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The Life of Tufu" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Eliot Weinberger, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238052&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Life of Tufu&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Oliver Munday (New Directions, April)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Life-of-Tufu-186x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Life-of-Tufu.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246592" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Life-of-Tufu.jpeg" alt="The Life of Tufu" width="621" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Life-of-Tufu.jpeg 621w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Life-of-Tufu-186x300.jpeg 186w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Life-of-Tufu-37x60.jpeg 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/The-Life-of-Tufu-31x50.jpeg 31w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 621px) 100vw, 621px" /></a> Eliot Weinberger, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238052" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Life of Tufu</a></em>; cover design by Oliver Munday (New Directions, April)</span>
<p>Just incredibly stylish and tasteful.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.katesinclair.space/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kate Sinclair</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593728727" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246513" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/on-freedom-design-suzanne-dean-art-anton-logov/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/on-freedom-design-suzanne-dean-art-anton-logov.jpg" data-orig-size="979,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="on freedom uk" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Timothy Snyder, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593728727&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;On Freedom&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Suzanne Dean, art by Anton Logov (Bodley Head, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/on-freedom-design-suzanne-dean-art-anton-logov-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/on-freedom-design-suzanne-dean-art-anton-logov-668x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246513" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/on-freedom-design-suzanne-dean-art-anton-logov-668x1024.jpg" alt="on freedom uk" width="668" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/on-freedom-design-suzanne-dean-art-anton-logov-668x1024.jpg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/on-freedom-design-suzanne-dean-art-anton-logov-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/on-freedom-design-suzanne-dean-art-anton-logov-768x1177.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/on-freedom-design-suzanne-dean-art-anton-logov-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/on-freedom-design-suzanne-dean-art-anton-logov-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/on-freedom-design-suzanne-dean-art-anton-logov.jpg 979w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 668px) 100vw, 668px" /></a> Timothy Snyder, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593728727" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">On Freedom</a></em>; cover design by Suzanne Dean, art by Anton Logov (Bodley Head, September)</span>
<p>This cover is a masterpiece of simplicity. Its striking art eliminates the need for a subtitle. It evokes the spirit of 1960s protest posters, brimming with raw, human energy. I love how the human-crafted essence shines through in both the art and composition. Honorable Dean mentions: <em>Dogs and Monsters</em>, the Murakami redesigns, <em>Paper Boat</em> by M. Atwood (unreal!), An Yu&#8217;s <em>Sunbirth</em>, etc&#8230; Suzanne has truly excelled this year!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://milanbozic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Milan Božić</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781566896931" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238914" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/fog-car-eugene-lim/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/fog-car-eugene-lim.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="fog &#038; car eugene lim" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Eugene Lim, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781566896931&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Fog &amp;amp; Car&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Michael Salu (Coffee House Press, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/fog-car-eugene-lim-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/fog-car-eugene-lim.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-238914" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/fog-car-eugene-lim.jpeg" alt="Eugene Lim, Fog &amp; Car" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/fog-car-eugene-lim.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/fog-car-eugene-lim-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/fog-car-eugene-lim-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/fog-car-eugene-lim-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Eugene Lim, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781566896931" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Fog &amp; Car</em></a>; cover design by Michael Salu (Coffee House Press, July)</span>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246600" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/fog-car-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fog-Car-2-scaled.jpeg" data-orig-size="2560,1690" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Fog &#038; Car 2" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fog-Car-2-300x198.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fog-Car-2-1240x819.jpeg" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-246600" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fog-Car-2-1240x819.jpeg" alt="" width="1240" height="819" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fog-Car-2-1240x819.jpeg 1240w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fog-Car-2-300x198.jpeg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fog-Car-2-768x507.jpeg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fog-Car-2-60x40.jpeg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fog-Car-2-1536x1014.jpeg 1536w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fog-Car-2-2048x1352.jpeg 2048w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fog-Car-2-50x33.jpeg 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1240px) 100vw, 1240px" /></p>
<p>I love the multivalent minimalism at work here. Combined with the back cover and spine, this is a lovely object all around. Leave it to Michael Salu to give us the unexpected.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://albanfischerdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alban Fischer</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781635902082" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246521" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/71ppevkhhhl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71PPEvkhhHL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="932,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="kate zambreno heroines uk" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Kate Zambreno, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781635902082&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Heroines&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Nico Taylor (Corsair, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71PPEvkhhHL._SL1500_-186x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71PPEvkhhHL._SL1500_-636x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246521" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71PPEvkhhHL._SL1500_-636x1024.jpg" alt="kate zambreno heroines uk" width="636" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71PPEvkhhHL._SL1500_-636x1024.jpg 636w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71PPEvkhhHL._SL1500_-186x300.jpg 186w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71PPEvkhhHL._SL1500_-768x1236.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71PPEvkhhHL._SL1500_-37x60.jpg 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71PPEvkhhHL._SL1500_-31x50.jpg 31w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71PPEvkhhHL._SL1500_.jpg 932w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 636px) 100vw, 636px" /></a> Kate Zambreno, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781635902082" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Heroines</a></em>; cover design by Nico Taylor (Corsair, July)</span>
<p>There&#8217;s an elegance to this cover that is combined with the confrontation of the eye contact photo and the chanting repeat of the type. The duality of feeling is incredibly striking.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jacksmyth.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jack Smyth</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780771006074" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246476" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/supplication-uk-design-luke-bird-scaled/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Supplication-UK-design-Luke-Bird-scaled-1.jpg" data-orig-size="1664,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="supplication luke bird" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Nour Abi-Nakhoul, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780771006074&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Supplication&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Luke Bird (Influx Press, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Supplication-UK-design-Luke-Bird-scaled-1-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Supplication-UK-design-Luke-Bird-scaled-1-666x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246476" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Supplication-UK-design-Luke-Bird-scaled-1-666x1024.jpg" alt="supplication luke bird" width="666" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Supplication-UK-design-Luke-Bird-scaled-1-666x1024.jpg 666w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Supplication-UK-design-Luke-Bird-scaled-1-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Supplication-UK-design-Luke-Bird-scaled-1-768x1182.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Supplication-UK-design-Luke-Bird-scaled-1-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Supplication-UK-design-Luke-Bird-scaled-1-998x1536.jpg 998w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Supplication-UK-design-Luke-Bird-scaled-1-1331x2048.jpg 1331w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Supplication-UK-design-Luke-Bird-scaled-1-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Supplication-UK-design-Luke-Bird-scaled-1.jpg 1664w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 666px) 100vw, 666px" /></a> Nour Abi-Nakhoul, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780771006074" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Supplication</a></em>; cover design by Luke Bird (Influx Press, June)</span>
<p>This looks like it comes from somewhere else. Nice to see a cover that stands out because, unlike everything else, it’s not colourful. I like how the image sits somewhere between being a photograph and a drawing and the reflection in the mirror tells us nothing.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.keenandesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jamie Keenan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246530" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/unnamed-223/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unnamed.jpg" data-orig-size="818,1280" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Chris Kohler phantom limb" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Chris Kohler, &lt;em&gt;Phantom Limb&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Holly Battle (Atlantic Books, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unnamed-192x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unnamed-654x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246530" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unnamed-654x1024.jpg" alt="Chris Kohler phantom limb" width="654" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unnamed-654x1024.jpg 654w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unnamed-192x300.jpg 192w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unnamed-768x1202.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unnamed-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unnamed-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/unnamed.jpg 818w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 654px) 100vw, 654px" /> Chris Kohler, <em>Phantom Limb</em>; cover design by Holly Battle (Atlantic Books, August)</span>
<p>Eerie &amp; intriguing, such a great use of negative space.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://annamorrison.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Anna Morrison</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781982186791" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246541" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/71iglcm-l-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71IgLcm-L._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="985,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="best american poetry 2024" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;David Lehman, Mary Jo Salter, eds., &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781982186791&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Best American Poetry 2024&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jaya Miceli (Scribner, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71IgLcm-L._SL1500_-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71IgLcm-L._SL1500_-672x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246541" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71IgLcm-L._SL1500_-672x1024.jpg" alt="best american poetry 2024" width="672" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71IgLcm-L._SL1500_-672x1024.jpg 672w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71IgLcm-L._SL1500_-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71IgLcm-L._SL1500_-768x1170.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71IgLcm-L._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71IgLcm-L._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71IgLcm-L._SL1500_.jpg 985w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 672px) 100vw, 672px" /></a> David Lehman, Mary Jo Salter, eds., <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781982186791" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Best American Poetry 2024</a></em>; cover design by Jaya Miceli (Scribner, September)</span>
<p>It&#8217;s always a treat to see which repeating geometric shapes and colors will anchor this series each year. On this cover, I love how the painting&#8217;s background blends with the flat tan color to chop those red shapes into sharp triangles.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://bendenzer.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Ben Denzer</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781922754233" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246623" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/eat-nyc-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/eat-nyc-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="785,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="eat nyc copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Yasmin Newman, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781922754233&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Eat NYC&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Evi-O. Studio (Smith Street Books, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/eat-nyc-copy-236x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/eat-nyc-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246623" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/eat-nyc-copy.jpg" alt="" width="785" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/eat-nyc-copy.jpg 785w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/eat-nyc-copy-236x300.jpg 236w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/eat-nyc-copy-768x978.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/eat-nyc-copy-47x60.jpg 47w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/eat-nyc-copy-39x50.jpg 39w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 785px) 100vw, 785px" /></a> Yasmin Newman, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781922754233" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Eat NYC</a></em>; cover design by Evi-O. Studio (Smith Street Books, October)</span>
<p>Everything about the packaging of this book is iconic NYC! From the illustrations, to the sprayed edges, to how the table of contents are laid out.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.laywankwan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Laywan Kwan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781538722374" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246524" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/tripping-on-utopia-design-tyler-comrie/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tripping-on-utopia-design-tyler-comrie.jpg" data-orig-size="1696,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="tripping on utopia" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Benjamin Breen, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781538722374&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Tripping on Utopia&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Tyler Comrie (Grand Central, January)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tripping-on-utopia-design-tyler-comrie-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tripping-on-utopia-design-tyler-comrie-678x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246524" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tripping-on-utopia-design-tyler-comrie-678x1024.jpg" alt="tripping on utopia" width="678" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tripping-on-utopia-design-tyler-comrie-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tripping-on-utopia-design-tyler-comrie-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tripping-on-utopia-design-tyler-comrie-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tripping-on-utopia-design-tyler-comrie-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tripping-on-utopia-design-tyler-comrie-1018x1536.jpg 1018w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tripping-on-utopia-design-tyler-comrie-1357x2048.jpg 1357w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tripping-on-utopia-design-tyler-comrie-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tripping-on-utopia-design-tyler-comrie.jpg 1696w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 678px) 100vw, 678px" /></a> Benjamin Breen, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781538722374" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Tripping on Utopia</a></em>; cover design by Tyler Comrie (Grand Central, January)</span>
<p>The type of cover that makes you go, “Damn it, I wish I designed this…”</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jayanicely.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jaya Nicely</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063337879" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239012" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/tony-tulathimutte-rejection/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Tony-Tulathimutte-Rejection-.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Tony Tulathimutte, Rejection" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Tony Tulathimutte, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063337879&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Rejection&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Ploy Siripant (William Morrow, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Tony-Tulathimutte-Rejection--200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Tony-Tulathimutte-Rejection-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239012" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Tony-Tulathimutte-Rejection-.jpeg" alt="Tony Tulathimutte, Rejection" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Tony-Tulathimutte-Rejection-.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Tony-Tulathimutte-Rejection--200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Tony-Tulathimutte-Rejection--40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Tony-Tulathimutte-Rejection--33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Tony Tulathimutte, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063337879" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Rejection</a></em>; cover design by Ploy Siripant (William Morrow, September)</span>
<p>The simplicity! I love a good fuzzy gradient.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.vivianrowe.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Vivian Lopez Rowe</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246738" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/in-memoriam/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/in-memoriam.jpeg" data-orig-size="648,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="in memoriam" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Alice Winn, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593467848&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;In Memoriam&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Madeline Partner (Knopf, March)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/in-memoriam-194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/in-memoriam.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246738" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/in-memoriam.jpeg" alt="in memoriam" width="648" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/in-memoriam.jpeg 648w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/in-memoriam-194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/in-memoriam-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/in-memoriam-32x50.jpeg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 648px) 100vw, 648px" /> Alice Winn, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593467848" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">In Memoriam</a></em>; cover design by Madeline Partner (Knopf, March)</span>
<p>Gorgeous use of white space. (Use your erase tool to knock out the quote bubble.)</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593801970" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239085" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/haruki-murakami-the-city-and-its-uncertain-walls/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Haruki-Murakami-The-City-and-Its-Uncertain-Walls-.jpeg" data-orig-size="680,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Haruki Murakami, The City and Its Uncertain Walls" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Haruki Murakami, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593801970&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The City and Its Uncertain Walls&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Chip Kidd (Knopf, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Haruki-Murakami-The-City-and-Its-Uncertain-Walls--204x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Haruki-Murakami-The-City-and-Its-Uncertain-Walls-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239085" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Haruki-Murakami-The-City-and-Its-Uncertain-Walls-.jpeg" alt="Haruki Murakami, The City and Its Uncertain Walls" width="680" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Haruki-Murakami-The-City-and-Its-Uncertain-Walls-.jpeg 680w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Haruki-Murakami-The-City-and-Its-Uncertain-Walls--204x300.jpeg 204w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Haruki-Murakami-The-City-and-Its-Uncertain-Walls--41x60.jpeg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Haruki-Murakami-The-City-and-Its-Uncertain-Walls--34x50.jpeg 34w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /></a> Haruki Murakami, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593801970" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The City and Its Uncertain Walls</a></em>; cover design by Chip Kidd (Knopf, November)</span>
<p>I included this cover because I’m so excited to read it! Murakami is one of my favorite authors. His work feels like a Southern Gothic style told through a Japanese lens, directed by David Lynch. <em>Jeopardy!</em>’s favorite book cover designer Chip Kidd really captures Murakami’s mysterious, yet human and relatable writing.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="http://www.pepcostudio.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Philip Pascuzzo</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781945492990" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246651" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/speakstop/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/speakstop.jpeg" data-orig-size="656,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="speak:stop" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Noémi Lefebvre, tr. Sophie Lewis, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781945492990&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Speak/Stop&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Transit Books, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/speakstop-197x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/speakstop.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246651" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/speakstop.jpeg" alt="speak:stop" width="656" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/speakstop.jpeg 656w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/speakstop-197x300.jpeg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/speakstop-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/speakstop-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 656px) 100vw, 656px" /></a> Noémi Lefebvre, tr. Sophie Lewis, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781945492990" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Speak/Stop</a></em>; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Transit Books, October)</span>
<p>I’m a sucker for an original combination of images done in such an offhand, spontaneous, casual style. Dare I say, timeless and fresh all at once.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.rachelakedesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Rachel Ake</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246583" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/71i4mcvsl0l-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71i4mcVsL0L._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="977,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Graham Caveney, &lt;em&gt;The Body in the Library&lt;/em&gt;" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Graham Caveney, &lt;em&gt;The Body in the Library&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by David Pearson (Peninsula Press, May)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71i4mcVsL0L._SL1500_-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71i4mcVsL0L._SL1500_-667x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246583" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71i4mcVsL0L._SL1500_-667x1024.jpg" alt="Graham Caveney, &lt;em&gt;The Body in the Library&lt;/em&gt;" width="667" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71i4mcVsL0L._SL1500_-667x1024.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71i4mcVsL0L._SL1500_-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71i4mcVsL0L._SL1500_-768x1179.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71i4mcVsL0L._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71i4mcVsL0L._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/71i4mcVsL0L._SL1500_.jpg 977w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /> Graham Caveney, <em>The Body in the Library</em>; cover design by David Pearson (Peninsula Press, May)</span>
<p>You never see a cover with a giant swan. I love it. I love how the swan is smushed and bent to fit in the space. Poor swan. The type marries sooooo nicely with the illustration style.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/robinbillz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Robin Bilardello</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593656563" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="240888" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-17-best-book-covers-of-july-2/anyones-ghost-august-thompson/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/anyones-ghost-august-thompson.jpg" data-orig-size="987,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="anyones ghost august thompson" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;August Thompson, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593656563&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Anyone&#8217;s Ghost&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Keith Hayes (Penguin Press, July)&lt;/p&gt;
