<p>The composition of the illustration, the limited palette–a beaut!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.hollyovenden.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Holly Ovenden</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316578929" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246626" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/a-salty-piece-of-land/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-salty-piece-of-land.jpeg" data-orig-size="645,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="a salty piece of land" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Jimmy Buffett, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316578929&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;A Salty Piece of Land&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt; (20th Anniversary Edition); cover design by Tim Green, art direction by Lucy Kim (Little, Brown, May)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-salty-piece-of-land-194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-salty-piece-of-land.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246626" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-salty-piece-of-land.jpeg" alt="a salty piece of land" width="645" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-salty-piece-of-land.jpeg 645w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-salty-piece-of-land-194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-salty-piece-of-land-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-salty-piece-of-land-32x50.jpeg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 645px) 100vw, 645px" /></a> Jimmy Buffett, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316578929" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">A Salty Piece of Land</a></em> (20th Anniversary Edition); cover design by Tim Green, art direction by Lucy Kim (Little, Brown, May)</span>
<p>This cover is so cool and groovy and weird and wonderful!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.laywankwan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Laywan Kwan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246459" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/tonks-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tonks.jpg" data-orig-size="900,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="tonks" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;The Rosemary Tonks series reissues, cover design by Matt Broughton, illustration by Fien Jorissen (Vintage Classics UK, May 2) &lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tonks-300x150.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tonks.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246459" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tonks.jpg" alt="" width="900" height="450" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tonks.jpg 900w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tonks-300x150.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tonks-768x384.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tonks-60x30.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tonks-50x25.jpg 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /> The Rosemary Tonks series reissues, cover design by Matt Broughton, illustration by Fien Jorissen (Vintage Classics UK, May 2)</span>
<p>Even with their 2D, flat illustrations, these covers feel incredibly dynamic, and I want to read these books knowing nothing about them. The curving type that envelops the illustrations are also really lovely!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kishanrajanidesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kishan Rajani</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781951971144" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246601" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/necrology/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/necrology.jpeg" data-orig-size="642,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="necrology" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Meg Ripley, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781951971144&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Necrology&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Luísa Dias (Creature Publishing, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/necrology-193x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/necrology.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246601" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/necrology.jpeg" alt="necrology" width="642" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/necrology.jpeg 642w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/necrology-193x300.jpeg 193w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/necrology-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/necrology-32x50.jpeg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 642px) 100vw, 642px" /></a> Meg Ripley, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781951971144" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Necrology</a></em>; cover design by Luísa Dias (Creature Publishing, September)</span>
<p>I&#8217;m not sure I&#8217;ve seen a horror cover quite like this. It gives horror via sly—almost inviting—touches of sinister dread. Effective and well-done.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://albanfischerdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alban Fischer</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781952119996" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238948" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/sam-sax-yr-dead/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/sam-sax-yr-dead.jpeg" data-orig-size="679,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="sam sax yr dead" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Sam Sax, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781952119996&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Yr Dead&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Andrea Settimo (McSweeney&#8217;s, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/sam-sax-yr-dead-204x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/sam-sax-yr-dead.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-238948" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/sam-sax-yr-dead.jpeg" alt="" width="679" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/sam-sax-yr-dead.jpeg 679w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/sam-sax-yr-dead-204x300.jpeg 204w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/sam-sax-yr-dead-41x60.jpeg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/sam-sax-yr-dead-34x50.jpeg 34w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px" /></a> Sam Sax, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781952119996" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Yr Dead</a></em>; cover design by Andrea Settimo (McSweeney&#8217;s, August)</span>
<p>Wow! Die-cut peepers too.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238649" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246589" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/marcel-proust-letters-to-his-neighbor/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/marcel-proust-letters-to-his-neighbor.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="marcel proust letters to his neighbor" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Marcel Proust, tr. Lydia Davis, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238649&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Letters to His Neighbor&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Tyler Comrie (New Directions, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/marcel-proust-letters-to-his-neighbor-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/marcel-proust-letters-to-his-neighbor.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246589" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/marcel-proust-letters-to-his-neighbor.jpeg" alt="marcel proust letters to his neighbor" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/marcel-proust-letters-to-his-neighbor.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/marcel-proust-letters-to-his-neighbor-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/marcel-proust-letters-to-his-neighbor-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/marcel-proust-letters-to-his-neighbor-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Marcel Proust, tr. Lydia Davis, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238649" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Letters to His Neighbor</a></em>; cover design by Tyler Comrie (New Directions, November)</span>
<p>All the type is on the stamps!! Perfection.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.nataliaolbinski.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Natalia Olbinski</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250357595" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246416" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/deadly-animals/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/deadly-animals-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1696,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="deadly animals" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Marie Tierney, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250357595&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Deadly Animals&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Emily Mahar (Henry Holt, November 12)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/deadly-animals-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/deadly-animals-678x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246416" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/deadly-animals-678x1024.jpg" alt="deadly animals" width="678" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/deadly-animals-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/deadly-animals-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/deadly-animals-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/deadly-animals-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/deadly-animals-1017x1536.jpg 1017w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/deadly-animals-1356x2048.jpg 1356w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/deadly-animals-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/deadly-animals-scaled.jpg 1696w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 678px) 100vw, 678px" /></a> Marie Tierney, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250357595" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Deadly Animals</a></em>; cover design by Emily Mahar (Henry Holt, November 12)</span>
<p>It&#8217;s one of those covers that just gives you chills when you see it, both beautiful and unsettling.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jennisurasky.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jenni Surasky</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593318119" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239156" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-15-best-book-covers-of-june/ask-me-again-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ask-me-again.jpeg" data-orig-size="682,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="ask me again" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Clare Sestanovich, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593318119&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Ask Me Again&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Janet Hansen (Knopf, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ask-me-again-205x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ask-me-again.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239156" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ask-me-again.jpeg" alt="" width="682" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ask-me-again.jpeg 682w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ask-me-again-205x300.jpeg 205w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ask-me-again-41x60.jpeg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ask-me-again-34x50.jpeg 34w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 682px) 100vw, 682px" /></a> Clare Sestanovich, <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593318119" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ask Me Again</a></em>; cover design by Janet Hansen (Knopf, June)</span>
<p>So unexpected. Jarring, in a really good way.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://dana-li.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Dana Li</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802162809" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246487" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/blue-maiden/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/blue-maiden.jpg" data-orig-size="676,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="blue maiden" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Anna Noyes, The Blue Maiden; cover design by Kelly Winton (Grove Press, May 14)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/blue-maiden-203x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/blue-maiden.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246487" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/blue-maiden.jpg" alt="" width="676" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/blue-maiden.jpg 676w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/blue-maiden-203x300.jpg 203w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/blue-maiden-41x60.jpg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/blue-maiden-34x50.jpg 34w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 676px) 100vw, 676px" /></a> Anna Noyes, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802162809" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Blue Maiden</a></em>; cover design by Kelly Winton (Grove Press, May)</span>
<p>I was immediately drawn to the craft in this design. Visually, the cover feels like it was composed by one or both of the story&#8217;s sisters, and conceptually, natural elements held in suspension works so well for the book’s themes. This elegantly eerie cover begs to be displayed face-out.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jasonarias.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jason Arias</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781945492846" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="231432" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024/71c65-ha2al-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71c65-HA2AL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="977,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Iman Mersal, tr. Robin Moger, Traces of Enayat" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Iman Mersal, tr. Robin Moger, &lt;em&gt;Traces of Enayat&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Anna Morrison (Transit Books, April 2)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71c65-HA2AL._SL1500_-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71c65-HA2AL._SL1500_-667x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-231432" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71c65-HA2AL._SL1500_-667x1024.jpg" alt="Iman Mersal, tr. Robin Moger, Traces of Enayat" width="667" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71c65-HA2AL._SL1500_-667x1024.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71c65-HA2AL._SL1500_-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71c65-HA2AL._SL1500_-768x1179.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71c65-HA2AL._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71c65-HA2AL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/71c65-HA2AL._SL1500_.jpg 977w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Iman Mersal, tr. Robin Moger, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781945492846" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Traces of Enayat</a></em>; cover design by Anna Morrison (Transit Books, April 2)</span>
<p>Such fantastic colour and texture.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.tometherington.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Tom Etherington</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593474549" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246586" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/love-cant-feed-you-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/love-cant-feed-you.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="love can&#8217;t feed you" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Cherry Lou Sy, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593474549&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Love Can&#8217;t Feed You&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Dominique Jones (Dutton, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/love-cant-feed-you-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/love-cant-feed-you.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246586" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/love-cant-feed-you.jpeg" alt="love can't feed you" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/love-cant-feed-you.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/love-cant-feed-you-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/love-cant-feed-you-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/love-cant-feed-you-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Cherry Lou Sy, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593474549" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Love Can&#8217;t Feed You</a></em>; cover design by Dominique Jones (Dutton, October)</span>
<p>I find something new to love in this design every time I revisit it. The colors, the textures, the scale(s), I love it all.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.morgankrehbiel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Morgan Krehbiel</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246478" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/81rcad0nzwl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81RCAD0nzwL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="933,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="birding" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Rose Ruane, &lt;em&gt;Birding&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Charlotte Stroomer (Corsair, May)&lt;/p&gt;
