<p>Clever mirroring of art and type.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="http://www.linda-huang.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Linda Huang</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="245697" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/871cdd_e3f10707b55d46948da4e6d7fb538f29mv2-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/871cdd_e3f10707b55d46948da4e6d7fb538f29mv2-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="516,793" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="above us the sea" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Ania Card, &lt;em&gt;Above Us the Sea&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Emma Ewbank (Dead Ink Books, July 11)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/871cdd_e3f10707b55d46948da4e6d7fb538f29mv2-copy-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/871cdd_e3f10707b55d46948da4e6d7fb538f29mv2-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-245697" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/871cdd_e3f10707b55d46948da4e6d7fb538f29mv2-copy.jpg" alt="above us the sea" width="516" height="793" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/871cdd_e3f10707b55d46948da4e6d7fb538f29mv2-copy.jpg 516w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/871cdd_e3f10707b55d46948da4e6d7fb538f29mv2-copy-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/871cdd_e3f10707b55d46948da4e6d7fb538f29mv2-copy-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/871cdd_e3f10707b55d46948da4e6d7fb538f29mv2-copy-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 516px) 100vw, 516px" /> Ania Card, <em>Above Us the Sea</em>; cover design by Emma Ewbank (Dead Ink Books, July)</span>
<p>The type is beautifully positioned to frame this arresting image.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.hollyovenden.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Holly Ovenden</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780812997118" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246460" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/712xhdjvzel-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/712xhdjVZEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="652,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="tremor uk" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Teju Cole, &lt;em&gt;Tremor&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Henry Petrides (Faber &#038; Faber, September 25)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/712xhdjVZEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/712xhdjVZEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246460" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/712xhdjVZEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="tremor uk" width="652" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/712xhdjVZEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 652w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/712xhdjVZEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/712xhdjVZEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/712xhdjVZEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px" /></a> Teju Cole, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780812997118" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Tremor</a></em>; cover design by Henry Petrides (Faber &amp; Faber, September)</span>
<p>Henry has designed the PB series for these, and they&#8217;re all brilliant, but <em>Tremor</em> is my favourite. This cover so brilliantly captures the entrancing, fleeting visuals that this book evokes. The ink-trap type on this cover is also super confident and striking.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kishanrajanidesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kishan Rajani</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250335807" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="245702" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/open-throat/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/open-throat.jpg" data-orig-size="750,1125" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="open throat" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Henry Hoke, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250335807&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Open Throat&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt; (paperback); design by Alex Merto, illustration by Matt Buck (Picador, June 4)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/open-throat-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/open-throat-683x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-245702" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/open-throat-683x1024.jpg" alt="" width="683" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/open-throat-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/open-throat-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/open-throat-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/open-throat-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/open-throat.jpg 750w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></a> Henry Hoke, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250335807" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Open Throat</a></em> (paperback); design by Alex Merto, illustration by Matt Buck (Picador, June)</span>
<p>The lion&#8217;s teeth-as-title is just brilliant. The neon pink really makes the whole cover come alive.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://sarahschulte.studio/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sarah Schulte</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781949641691" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239055" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/johannes-anyuru-tr-nichola-smalley-ixelles/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Johannes-Anyuru-tr.-Nichola-Smalley-Ixelles-.jpeg" data-orig-size="647,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Johannes Anyuru, tr. Nichola Smalley, Ixelles" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Johannes Anyuru, tr. Nichola Smalley, &lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781949641691&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ixelles&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Jonathan Pelham (Two Lines Press, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Johannes-Anyuru-tr.-Nichola-Smalley-Ixelles--194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Johannes-Anyuru-tr.-Nichola-Smalley-Ixelles-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239055" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Johannes-Anyuru-tr.-Nichola-Smalley-Ixelles-.jpeg" alt="Johannes Anyuru, tr. Nichola Smalley, Ixelles" width="647" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Johannes-Anyuru-tr.-Nichola-Smalley-Ixelles-.jpeg 647w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Johannes-Anyuru-tr.-Nichola-Smalley-Ixelles--194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Johannes-Anyuru-tr.-Nichola-Smalley-Ixelles--39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Johannes-Anyuru-tr.-Nichola-Smalley-Ixelles--32x50.jpeg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 647px) 100vw, 647px" /></a> Johannes Anyuru, tr. Nichola Smalley, <a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781949641691" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Ixelles</em></a>; cover design by Jonathan Pelham (Two Lines Press, October)</span>
<p>This is another cover that brought me to the purchase page to find out about the yellow shape which represents a golden cd that seems to be part of a pivotal moment within the text. Another juxtaposition of a modern clean element with a textured lush painting creating gorgeous tension and interest and a cover that stands out.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.nicolecaputo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Nicole Caputo</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781638932871" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246508" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/throwback/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Throwback.jpg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Throwback" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Maureen Goo, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781638932871&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Throwback&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; paperback redesign by Jenna Stempel-Lobell (Zando Young Readers, December)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Throwback-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Throwback.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246508" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Throwback.jpg" alt="" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Throwback.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Throwback-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Throwback-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Throwback-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Maureen Goo, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781638932871" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Throwback</a></em>; paperback redesign by Jenna Stempel-Lobell (Zando Young Readers, December)</span>
<p>A paperback redesign that stops you in your tracks.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.casandragonzales.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Cassie Gonzales Vu</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781945492853" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246511" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/novices-of-lerna/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/novices-of-lerna.jpg" data-orig-size="656,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="novices of lerna" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Ángel Bonomini, tr. Jordan Landsman, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781945492853&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Novices of Lerna&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Transit Books, May)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/novices-of-lerna-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/novices-of-lerna.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246511" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/novices-of-lerna.jpg" alt="novices of lerna" width="656" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/novices-of-lerna.jpg 656w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/novices-of-lerna-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/novices-of-lerna-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/novices-of-lerna-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 656px) 100vw, 656px" /></a> Ángel Bonomini, tr. Jordan Landsman, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781945492853" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Novices of Lerna</a></em>; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Transit Books, May)</span>
<p>Such a great example of an organic illustration and hand lettering working together harmoniously. The limited color palette makes the cover even more striking.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kimberlyglyder.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kimberly Glyder</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063299665" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246418" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/dinner-on-monster-island/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dinner-on-monster-island.jpg" data-orig-size="663,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="dinner on monster island" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Tania De Rosario, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063299665&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Dinner on Monster Island&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Olivia McGiff (Harper Perennial, February 6)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dinner-on-monster-island-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dinner-on-monster-island.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246418" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dinner-on-monster-island.jpg" alt="dinner on monster island" width="663" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dinner-on-monster-island.jpg 663w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dinner-on-monster-island-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dinner-on-monster-island-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dinner-on-monster-island-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 663px) 100vw, 663px" /></a> Tania De Rosario, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063299665" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Dinner on Monster Island</a></em>; cover design by Olivia McGiff (Harper Perennial, February)</span>
<p>Scary-beautiful! I love the unique composition and the texture.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://joannemoneill.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Joanne O&#8217;Neill</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781550656572" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246488" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/national-animal/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/national-animal.jpg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="national animal" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Derek Webster, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781550656572&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;National Animal&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by David Drummond (Signal Editions, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/national-animal-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/national-animal.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246488" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/national-animal.jpg" alt="national animal" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/national-animal.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/national-animal-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/national-animal-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/national-animal-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Derek Webster, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781550656572" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">National Animal</a></em>; cover design by David Drummond (Signal Editions, September)</span>
<p>I am mesmerized by this shape-shifting sculpture, how it’s made of metal, but feels more like it’s composed of air, water, or even fire. It’s poetic in its own right while also capturing the collection’s theme. I take this one as a pleasant reminder that book covers don’t have to bring the energy of a theater kid during a manic episode to be memorable. Nothing against theater kids.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jasonarias.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jason Arias</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781419773518" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="245972" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/715l1vw2rql-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/715l1VW2RQL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="973,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="715l1VW2RQL._SL1500_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Myriam Lacroix, &lt;em&gt;How it Works Out&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Luke Bird (Jonathan Cape, January 1)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/715l1VW2RQL._SL1500_-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/715l1VW2RQL._SL1500_-664x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-245972" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/715l1VW2RQL._SL1500_-664x1024.jpg" alt="" width="664" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/715l1VW2RQL._SL1500_-664x1024.jpg 664w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/715l1VW2RQL._SL1500_-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/715l1VW2RQL._SL1500_-768x1184.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/715l1VW2RQL._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/715l1VW2RQL._SL1500_-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/715l1VW2RQL._SL1500_.jpg 973w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 664px) 100vw, 664px" /></a> Myriam Lacroix, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781419773518" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">How it Works Out</a></em>; cover design by Luke Bird (Jonathan Cape, January)</span>
<p>I love the reverse contrast on the type against a white background, the brutal cleanliness works so well with the severed finger.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.tometherington.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Tom Etherington</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063330733" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="245553" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/the-tyranny-of-flies/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/the-tyranny-of-flies.jpg" data-orig-size="673,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="the tyranny of flies" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Elaine Vilar Madruga, tr. &lt;em&gt;The Tyranny of Flies&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Matt Dorfman (HarperVia, June 25)&lt;/p&gt;
