" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/let-me-liberate-you-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/let-me-liberate-you.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246591" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/let-me-liberate-you.jpeg" alt="let me liberate you" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/let-me-liberate-you.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/let-me-liberate-you-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/let-me-liberate-you-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/let-me-liberate-you-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Andie Davis, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662518416" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Let Me Liberate You</a></em>; cover design by Sarah Kellogg (Little a, July)</span>
<p>The colors, the patterns, the movement!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://dana-li.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Dana Li</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246602" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/1-1-5/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-1.jpg" data-orig-size="900,1399" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="1-1" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Boethius, &lt;em&gt;Poems from On the Consolation of Philosophy&lt;/em&gt;; art direction by Andrew Bourne (World Poetry, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-1-193x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-1-659x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246602" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-1-659x1024.jpg" alt="" width="659" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-1-659x1024.jpg 659w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-1-193x300.jpg 193w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-1-768x1194.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-1-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-1-32x50.jpg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/1-1.jpg 900w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 659px) 100vw, 659px" /> Boethius, <em>Poems from On the Consolation of Philosophy</em>; cover design by Andrew Bourne (World Poetry, November)</span>
<p>Andrew Bourne continues World Poetry’s run of stunning book designs. The cut-up type here is the perfect analogue to the translator&#8217;s approach in reshaping a centuries-old work.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://albanfischerdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alban Fischer</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781644453155" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246237" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-10-best-book-covers-of-november-4/version-1-0-0-9/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/81GVKJQ9wtL.jpg" data-orig-size="1707,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="taiwan travelogue" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Yáng Shuāng-zǐ, tr. Lin King, &lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781644453155&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Taiwan Travelogue&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Kimberly Glyder (Graywolf, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/81GVKJQ9wtL-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/81GVKJQ9wtL-683x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246237" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/81GVKJQ9wtL-683x1024.jpg" alt="taiwan travelogue" width="683" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/81GVKJQ9wtL-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/81GVKJQ9wtL-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/81GVKJQ9wtL-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/81GVKJQ9wtL-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/81GVKJQ9wtL-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/81GVKJQ9wtL-1366x2048.jpg 1366w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/81GVKJQ9wtL-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/81GVKJQ9wtL.jpg 1707w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></a> Yáng Shuāng-zǐ, tr. Lin King, <a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781644453155" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Taiwan Travelogue</em></a>; cover design by Kimberly Glyder (Graywolf, November)</span>
<p>The collaging of textures, artwork and photography gives warmth and richness to a seemingly very simple composition. Like the very best design, the result looks effortless.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jayanicely.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jaya Nicely</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246461" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/weird-fiction-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weird-fiction-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="900,911" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="weird fiction copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;The Penguin Weird Fiction series; design by Chris Bentham, illustrations by Kate Dehler (Penguin UK, October 17)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weird-fiction-copy-296x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weird-fiction-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246461" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weird-fiction-copy.jpg" alt="" width="900" height="911" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weird-fiction-copy.jpg 900w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weird-fiction-copy-296x300.jpg 296w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weird-fiction-copy-768x777.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weird-fiction-copy-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weird-fiction-copy-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weird-fiction-copy-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/weird-fiction-copy-50x50.jpg 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /> The Penguin Weird Fiction series; design by Chris Bentham, illustrations by Kate Dehler (Penguin UK, October)</span>
<p>All the covers I&#8217;ve seen in this series have been so bold, colourful and captivating, I love them!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kishanrajanidesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kishan Rajani</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316276177" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246528" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/ask-not-maureen-callahan/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ask-not-maureen-callahan.jpeg" data-orig-size="645,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="ask not maureen callahan" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Maureen Callahan, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316276177&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Ask Not&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Lucy Kim (Little, Brown, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ask-not-maureen-callahan-194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ask-not-maureen-callahan.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246528" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ask-not-maureen-callahan.jpeg" alt="ask not maureen callahan" width="645" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ask-not-maureen-callahan.jpeg 645w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ask-not-maureen-callahan-194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ask-not-maureen-callahan-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ask-not-maureen-callahan-32x50.jpeg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 645px) 100vw, 645px" /></a> Maureen Callahan, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316276177" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Ask Not</a></em>; cover design by Lucy Kim (Little, Brown, July)</span>
<p>Three immediately recognizable women, and an evocative title make such a strong design. You want to ask them and know the story through their eyes.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://laurenharms.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lauren Harms</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781324076360" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="243335" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-16-best-book-covers-of-september/91nqant-wkl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/91nQanT-WkL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="988,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Katherine Packert Burke, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781324076360&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Still Life&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sarahmay Wilkinson (Norton, September 10)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Katherine Packert Burke, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781324076360&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Still Life&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sarahmay Wilkinson (Norton, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/91nQanT-WkL._SL1500_-198x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/91nQanT-WkL._SL1500_-674x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-243335" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/91nQanT-WkL._SL1500_-674x1024.jpg" alt="Katherine Packert Burke, Still Life; cover design by Sarahmay Wilkinson (Norton, September 10)" width="674" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/91nQanT-WkL._SL1500_-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/91nQanT-WkL._SL1500_-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/91nQanT-WkL._SL1500_-768x1166.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/91nQanT-WkL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/91nQanT-WkL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/91nQanT-WkL._SL1500_.jpg 988w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px" /></a> Katherine Packert Burke, <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781324076360" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Still Life</a></em>; cover design by Sarahmay Wilkinson (Norton, September)</span>
<p>I bought this in a real life bookstore when I saw it. I was like POW I gotta have that. Also, maaannnnnn, how she’d get that approved. Dang.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/robinbillz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Robin Bilardello</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593706558" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239076" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/marisha-pessl-darkly/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Marisha-Pessl-Darkly-.jpeg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Marisha Pessl, Darkly" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Marisha Pessl, &lt;em&gt;Darkly&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Casey Moses (Delacorte Press, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Marisha-Pessl-Darkly--199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Marisha-Pessl-Darkly-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239076" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Marisha-Pessl-Darkly-.jpeg" alt="Marisha Pessl, Darkly" width="662" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Marisha-Pessl-Darkly-.jpeg 662w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Marisha-Pessl-Darkly--199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Marisha-Pessl-Darkly--40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Marisha-Pessl-Darkly--33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px" /></a> Marisha Pessl, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593706558" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Darkly</a></em>; cover design by Casey Moses (Delacorte Press, November)</span>
<p>It reminds me of rainbow scratch art from childhood!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.casandragonzales.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Cassie Gonzales Vu</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://shop.flammeforlag.no/collections/boker/products/blindernveien-4" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="245973" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/f537_blinderveien4_1024x1024-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/F537_Blinderveien4_1024x1024-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="597,1024" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="F537_Blinderveien4_1024x1024 copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Ellen Mari Thelle, &lt;em&gt;Blindernveien 4&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Aslak Gurholt (Flamme Forlag)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/F537_Blinderveien4_1024x1024-copy-175x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/F537_Blinderveien4_1024x1024-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-245973" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/F537_Blinderveien4_1024x1024-copy.jpg" alt="" width="597" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/F537_Blinderveien4_1024x1024-copy.jpg 597w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/F537_Blinderveien4_1024x1024-copy-175x300.jpg 175w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/F537_Blinderveien4_1024x1024-copy-35x60.jpg 35w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/F537_Blinderveien4_1024x1024-copy-29x50.jpg 29w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 597px) 100vw, 597px" /></a> Ellen Mari Thelle, <em>Blindernveien 4</em>; cover design by Aslak Gurholt (Flamme Forlag)</span>
<p>Aslak Gurholt designs all the books for Norwegian publisher Flamme Forlag, whose covers remind me more of record companies like Factory and ECM than publishers. There is stripped back, minimal aesthetic that runs through all of the covers designed by Gurholt for Flamme, without it ever becoming a ridged template. In an increasingly sales driven industry, it’s refreshing to see a publisher do something so unique and interesting.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.tometherington.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Tom Etherington</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246497" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/atwood-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/atwood-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="712,880" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="atwood copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Margaret Atwood, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593802649&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Paper Boat&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; design by Suzanne Dean, paper art by Nathan Ward (Vintage UK, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/atwood-copy-243x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/atwood-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246497" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/atwood-copy.jpg" alt="" width="712" height="880" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/atwood-copy.jpg 712w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/atwood-copy-243x300.jpg 243w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/atwood-copy-49x60.jpg 49w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/atwood-copy-40x50.jpg 40w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 712px) 100vw, 712px" /> Margaret Atwood, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593802649" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Paper Boat</a></em>; design by Suzanne Dean, paper art by Nathan Ward (Vintage UK, October)</span>
<p>Covers that transcend their main purpose will always capture my heart. This kind of design thinking buoys publishers among the POD squall.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jasonarias.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jason Arias</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780500027967" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="245552" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/51lkk3i8fnl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/51lKK3i8FnL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="997,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="point line plane" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Kengo Kuma, &lt;em&gt;Point Line Plane&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
