<p>Gorgeous and dreamy. The color palette feels unique and fresh.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://sarahschulte.studio/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sarah Schulte</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239499" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/sergio-de-la-pava-every-arc-bends-its-radian/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Sergio-de-la-Pava-Every-Arc-Bends-its-Radian-.jpeg" data-orig-size="652,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Sergio de la Pava, Every Arc Bends its Radian" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Sergio de la Pava, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668056707&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Every Arc Bends Its Radian&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by TK TK (Simon &amp;amp; Schuster, November 12)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Sergio-de-la-Pava-Every-Arc-Bends-its-Radian--196x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Sergio-de-la-Pava-Every-Arc-Bends-its-Radian-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239499" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Sergio-de-la-Pava-Every-Arc-Bends-its-Radian-.jpeg" alt="Sergio de la Pava, Every Arc Bends its Radian" width="652" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Sergio-de-la-Pava-Every-Arc-Bends-its-Radian-.jpeg 652w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Sergio-de-la-Pava-Every-Arc-Bends-its-Radian--196x300.jpeg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Sergio-de-la-Pava-Every-Arc-Bends-its-Radian--39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Sergio-de-la-Pava-Every-Arc-Bends-its-Radian--33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px" /> Sergio de la Pava, <em><a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668056707" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Every Arc Bends Its Radian</a></em>; cover design by Natalia Olbinski (Simon &amp; Schuster, November)</span>
<p>I&#8217;m obsessed with the curved type on this cover. It really leads your eyes across the entire design.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jennisurasky.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jenni Surasky</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237642" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246509" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/81p7y0j9rkl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/81P7y0J9RKL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="953,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Sylvia Legris" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Sylvia Legris, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237642&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Principle of Rapid Peering&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Ben Prior (Corsair, May)&lt;/p&gt;
