<p>Subtle and simply beautiful.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.casandragonzales.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Cassie Gonzales Vu</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063346574" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239392" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/willy-vlautin-the-horse/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Willy-Vlautin-The-Horse-.jpeg" data-orig-size="663,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Willy Vlautin, The Horse" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Willy Vlautin, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063346574&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Horse&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Milan Bozic (Harper, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Willy-Vlautin-The-Horse--199x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Willy-Vlautin-The-Horse-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-239392" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Willy-Vlautin-The-Horse-.jpeg" alt="Willy Vlautin, The Horse" width="663" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Willy-Vlautin-The-Horse-.jpeg 663w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Willy-Vlautin-The-Horse--199x300.jpeg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Willy-Vlautin-The-Horse--40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Willy-Vlautin-The-Horse--33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 663px) 100vw, 663px" /></a> Willy Vlautin, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063346574" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Horse</em></a>; cover design by Milan Bozic (Harper, July)</span>
<p>My daughter brought this book over to me in a bookstore and said, “I like this one because I like horses and I like orange juice.”</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/robinbillz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Robin Bilardello</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602177" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246539" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/91gcho39esl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/91gcHO39eSL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="91gcHO39eSL._SL1500_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;S.H. Fernando Jr., &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602177&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Chronicles of Doom&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by LAmour Supreme (Astra House, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/91gcHO39eSL._SL1500_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/91gcHO39eSL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246539" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/91gcHO39eSL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg" alt="" width="683" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/91gcHO39eSL._SL1500_-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/91gcHO39eSL._SL1500_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/91gcHO39eSL._SL1500_-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/91gcHO39eSL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/91gcHO39eSL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/91gcHO39eSL._SL1500_.jpg 1000w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px" /></a> S.H. Fernando Jr., <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602177" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Chronicles of Doom</a></em>; cover design by LAmour Supreme (Astra House, October)</span>
<p>All about this comic book treatment and its details. The artist’s seal of approval on the top right is genius.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.stephenbrayda.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Stephen Brayda</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246474" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/rothfuss-bundle/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rothfuss-bundle.jpg" data-orig-size="900,900" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="rothfuss bundle" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Patrick Rothfuss, The &lt;em&gt;Kingkiller Chronicles&lt;/em&gt; set redesign; cover design by Micaela Alcaino (Gollancz UK, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rothfuss-bundle-300x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rothfuss-bundle.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246474" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rothfuss-bundle.jpg" alt="" width="900" height="900" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rothfuss-bundle.jpg 900w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rothfuss-bundle-300x300.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rothfuss-bundle-150x150.jpg 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rothfuss-bundle-768x768.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rothfuss-bundle-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rothfuss-bundle-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rothfuss-bundle-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rothfuss-bundle-600x600.jpg 600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rothfuss-bundle-50x50.jpg 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /> Patrick Rothfuss, The <em>Kingkiller Chronicles</em> set redesign; cover design by Micaela Alcaino (Gollancz UK, June)</span>
<p>Micaela&#8217;s redesign of these books is nothing short of masterful. Each cover is brimming with intricately illustrated elements that seamlessly come together in perfect harmony. These designs are truly captivating, inviting you to pause and savor every stunning detail.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kishanrajanidesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kishan Rajani</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237185" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="233671" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-11-best-book-covers-of-february-2/71iz96clmxl-_sl1200_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/71iZ96clMXL._SL1200_.jpg" data-orig-size="778,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="71iZ96clMXL._SL1200_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Liliana Colanzi, tr. Chris Andrews, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811237185&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;You Glow in the Dark&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Jamie Keenan (New Directions, February )&lt;/p&gt;
