<p>I love the evocative combination of image and title.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://sross.tumblr.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Stephanie Ross</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781804296592" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246214" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-10-best-book-covers-of-november-4/the-absence-of-myth/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/the-absence-of-myth.jpg" data-orig-size="652,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="the absence of myth" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Georges Bataille, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781804296592&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Absence of Myth&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (reissue); cover design by Matt Dorfman (Verso, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/the-absence-of-myth-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/the-absence-of-myth.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-246214" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/the-absence-of-myth.jpg" alt="the absence of myth" width="652" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/the-absence-of-myth.jpg 652w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/the-absence-of-myth-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/the-absence-of-myth-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/the-absence-of-myth-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px" /></a> Georges Bataille, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781804296592" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Absence of Myth</em></a> (reissue); cover design by Matt Dorfman (Verso, November)</span>
<p>Love the use of clip art and playful type.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jayamiceli.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jaya Miceli</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668034927" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="238992" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/cebo-campbell-sky-full-of-elephants/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Cebo-Campbell-Sky-Full-of-Elephants.jpeg" data-orig-size="658,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Cebo Campbell, Sky Full of Elephants" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Cebo Campbell, &lt;em&gt;Sky Full of Elephants&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Tyler Comrie (Simon &#038; Schuster, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Cebo-Campbell-Sky-Full-of-Elephants-197x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Cebo-Campbell-Sky-Full-of-Elephants.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-238992" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Cebo-Campbell-Sky-Full-of-Elephants.jpeg" alt="Cebo Campbell, Sky Full of Elephants" width="658" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Cebo-Campbell-Sky-Full-of-Elephants.jpeg 658w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Cebo-Campbell-Sky-Full-of-Elephants-197x300.jpeg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Cebo-Campbell-Sky-Full-of-Elephants-39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Cebo-Campbell-Sky-Full-of-Elephants-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 658px) 100vw, 658px" /></a> Cebo Campbell, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668034927" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sky Full of Elephants</a></em>; cover design by Tyler Comrie (Simon &amp; Schuster, September)</span>
<p>Such energy! Everything about this is bold, and pulls me in. Great palette too.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://davidlitmandesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">David Litman</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602368" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="232529" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-12-best-book-covers-of-january-2/71i4k3gxk6l-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/71i4K3GxK6L._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="994,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Kōhei Saitō, tr. Brian Bergstrom, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602368&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Slow Down: The Degrowth Manifesto&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by TK TK (Astra House, January 9)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Kōhei Saitō, tr. Brian Bergstrom, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602368&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Slow Down: The Degrowth Manifesto&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Ben Denzer (Astra House, January)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/71i4K3GxK6L._SL1500_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/71i4K3GxK6L._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-232529" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/71i4K3GxK6L._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg" alt="Kōhei Saitō, tr. Brian Bergstrom, Slow Down: The Degrowth Manifesto; cover design by TK TK (Astra House, January 9)" width="679" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/71i4K3GxK6L._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg 679w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/71i4K3GxK6L._SL1500_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/71i4K3GxK6L._SL1500_-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/71i4K3GxK6L._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/71i4K3GxK6L._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/71i4K3GxK6L._SL1500_.jpg 994w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 679px) 100vw, 679px" /></a> Kōhei Saitō, tr. Brian Bergstrom, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602368" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Slow Down: The Degrowth Manifesto</a></em>; cover design by Ben Denzer (Astra House, January)</span>
<p>The infinite books on books is done so well here. Wonderfully simple.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://sross.tumblr.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Stephanie Ross</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246695" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/dogs-and-monsters-design-suzanne-dean-illus-neue-gestaltung-scaled/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dogs-and-monsters-design-suzanne-dean-illus-neue-gestaltung-scaled-1.jpg" data-orig-size="1672,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="dogs and monsters uk" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Mark Haddon, &lt;em&gt;Dogs and Monsters&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Suzanne Dean, illustration by Neue Gestaltung (Vintage UK, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dogs-and-monsters-design-suzanne-dean-illus-neue-gestaltung-scaled-1-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dogs-and-monsters-design-suzanne-dean-illus-neue-gestaltung-scaled-1-669x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246695" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dogs-and-monsters-design-suzanne-dean-illus-neue-gestaltung-scaled-1-669x1024.jpg" alt="dogs and monsters uk" width="669" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dogs-and-monsters-design-suzanne-dean-illus-neue-gestaltung-scaled-1-669x1024.jpg 669w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dogs-and-monsters-design-suzanne-dean-illus-neue-gestaltung-scaled-1-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dogs-and-monsters-design-suzanne-dean-illus-neue-gestaltung-scaled-1-768x1176.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dogs-and-monsters-design-suzanne-dean-illus-neue-gestaltung-scaled-1-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dogs-and-monsters-design-suzanne-dean-illus-neue-gestaltung-scaled-1-1003x1536.jpg 1003w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dogs-and-monsters-design-suzanne-dean-illus-neue-gestaltung-scaled-1-1338x2048.jpg 1338w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dogs-and-monsters-design-suzanne-dean-illus-neue-gestaltung-scaled-1-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/dogs-and-monsters-design-suzanne-dean-illus-neue-gestaltung-scaled-1.jpg 1672w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 669px) 100vw, 669px" /> Mark Haddon, <em>Dogs and Monsters</em>; cover design by Suzanne Dean, illustration by Neue Gestaltung (Vintage UK, August)</span>
<p>So bold and striking.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jayamiceli.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jaya Miceli</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781324086680" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246700" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/the-seventh-floor/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-seventh-floor.jpeg" data-orig-size="666,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="the seventh floor" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;David McCloskey, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781324086680&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The Seventh Floor&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Pete Garceau (W.W. Norton, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-seventh-floor-200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-seventh-floor.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246700" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-seventh-floor.jpeg" alt="the seventh floor" width="666" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-seventh-floor.jpeg 666w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-seventh-floor-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-seventh-floor-40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/the-seventh-floor-33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 666px) 100vw, 666px" /></a> David McCloskey, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781324086680" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Seventh Floor</a></em>; cover design by Pete Garceau (W.W. Norton, October)</span>
<p>My favorite spy novel cover this year. Pete created a fresh and simple series look!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jamesiacobelli.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">James Iacobelli</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781635425390" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246696" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth.jpg" data-orig-size="1600,2456" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Nanae Aoyama, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781635425390&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;A Perfect Day to Be Alone&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jack Smyth (Quercus, May)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth-667x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246696" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth-667x1024.jpg" alt="a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth" width="667" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth-667x1024.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth-768x1179.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth-1001x1536.jpg 1001w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth-1334x2048.jpg 1334w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/a-perfect-day-to-be-alone-design-jack-smyth.jpg 1600w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Nanae Aoyama, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781635425390" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">A Perfect Day to Be Alone</a></em>; cover design by Jack Smyth (Quercus, May)</span>
<p>Clever and warm.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jayamiceli.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jaya Miceli</a></em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Ironic Consolation Prize:</strong></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246739" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-167-best-book-covers-of-2024/collectors-edition-1/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1.jpg" data-orig-size="1520,1520" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="collectors-edition (1)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Melania Trump, &lt;em&gt;Melania&lt;/em&gt; (Collector’s Edition) ($250); cover design by ???&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1-300x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1-1024x1024.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-246739" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="1024" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1-300x300.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1-150x150.jpg 150w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1-768x768.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1-60x60.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1-109x109.jpg 109w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1-100x100.jpg 100w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1-600x600.jpg 600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1-50x50.jpg 50w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/collectors-edition-1.jpg 1520w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /> Melania Trump, <em>Melania</em> (Collector’s Edition) ($250); cover design by ??? (Skyhorse, October)</span>
<p>“I acknowledge that differing viewpoints are a natural aspect of human relationships.”</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markabramsbookdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
										
																				
																		
